title: pumpkin pancakes
directions: Sift together the first 7 ingredients.
Beat the next 5 ingredients together, then blend into dry ingredients.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle. Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look dark.
Serve immediately.
Yields 20 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Whip condensed milk and lemon juice together; add lemonade and peel.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts.
Makes two 8-inch pies or 1 extra serving size.
Use baked pie crust or graham cracker or vanilla wafer crusts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add bacon and potatoes, tossing lightly.
Beat thoroughly about 10 minutes.
Trim with parsley and pimiento, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain
salmon.
In
a
mixing bowl, mix salmon, egg and onion. Stir
in
flour.
Add
baking powder and 2 tablespoons milk to salmon mixture.
Form into small patties and fry until golden brown (about 5 minutes) in hot shortening.

title: rice a' go-go
directions: About 1 hour before serving, start heating oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water, stirring while dissolving.
In hot margarine in medium skillet (medium heat), saute rice for 5 minutes or until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add to broth in casserole.
Add rice, onion, celery, mushrooms and seasonings.
Bake, covered, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes.
Remove lid and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8 or more.

title: deviled crab
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients.
Place in small aluminum bake cups and bake at 450° for 40 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Cook 30 minutes and pack in clean jars and seal.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Add beaten egg yolks and milk. After mixing well, cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Now add in vanilla, butter and coconut, reserving a little of the coconut to sprinkle over top of meringue.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on top of pie. Sprinkle coconut on top and brown at 425°.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed on packages.
Add pineapple juice, bananas and strawberries.
Add sugar; mix well.
Freeze. Approximately 1 hour before serving, let thaw until slush.
Add ginger ale.
Serves 40 to 50 people.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast, milk and 1/2 cup sugar in saucepan and heat until lukewarm.
In large bowl, put flour, Crisco salt, eggs and rest of sugar.
Add the yeast mixture and work it up.
Get another large bowl and oil it.
Put dough in this bowl and knock it down.
Cover with wax paper and towel and put in warm place for 1 1/2 hours. After rising, knock it down and roll it around in the oil.
Make out rolls and put in greased pan.
Pat melted butter on top and bake at 350° until brown.
Brush with butter.

title: chicken and ham casserole
directions: Cook the onion in butter for 5 minutes, stirring constantly; do not let brown.
Add the mushrooms and seasonings and simmer 15 minutes.
Turn the mixture into oblong baking dish and arrange chicken and ham on top.
Add enough hot cream to cover the meat. Let simmer in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Cover with Parmesan cheese; let remain in oven until cheese is browned.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate a couple of hours before using.
It's a great relish tray dip.

title: fruit bars
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Cream butter with brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs and orange juice.
Add the flour mixture a little at a time, then fruits and nuts.
When mixed, turn into wax paper-lined pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy beef dip
directions: *Can use low-fat or no fat varieties.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers; do not crush.
May have to break a couple to fit around the pan.
Make pudding using 3 cups of milk.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Layer pudding with graham crackers, ending with crackers (3 layers crackers, 2 layers pudding).
Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: apple crunch
directions: Slice apples in
9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Sprinkle 1/2 of brown sugar and cinnamon mixture over apples.
Mix white sugar, flour, egg and baking powder together.
Mixture will be crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Drizzle 1 stick melted oleo over all.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar for 10 minutes; boil.
Remove from heat. Add butter, chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until cool.

title: sausage 'n' cabbage soup
directions: In a large kettle, over high heat, cook beef and sausage until brown.
Add cabbage and carrots.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring often. Drain.
Stir in soups, water and potatoes.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 10 to 15 minutes, or until carrots and potatoes are tender.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: scottish trifle(serves large crowd!)
directions: The key to this delicious traditional dessert is allowing each layer to set fully before proceeding to the next.
So allow yourself 48 hours in its preparation.

title: meal-in-a-casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line corned beef into greased pie plate and form into a nest.
Combine corn, soup, chopped onion and parsley.
Pour into nest.
Top with cheese and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Stir
dry
ingredients;
set aside.
Measure cereal and milk into
large
mixing bowl.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Add egg whites and
oil; beat well.
Stir in cranberries, raisins and orange peel.
Add dry ingredients	to cereal mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for 22 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: easy breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread slices on both sides.
Place 6 slices in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with layers of cheese, meat and onion. Top with remaining 6 slices of bread. Beat eggs.
Mix in milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight (or all day).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan.
Saute onions and green peppers until onion is transparent.
Remove from pan.
Cook chicken in butter (salt and pepper to taste) until done.
Remove chicken. Drain juice from can of peas into a measuring cup.
Add water to pea juice to measure for amount of rice you are cooking.
Pour into pan and follow directions for cooking rice.
When rice is cooked, add green pepper, onion, chicken and peas.
Mix well and serve.

title: ham and cheese brunch dish
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place half of bread cubes in dish.
Layer half of cheeses and ham and repeat layers with remaining cheese and ham.
Top with remaining bread cubes.
Beat together eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour liquid ingredients over mixture in dish and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, melt butter and mix with crushed corn flakes.
Spread on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: avocado-tomato soup
directions: Heat and pour over chipped up avocados in bottom of soup bowl or cup.

title: cooked chocolate icing
directions: Combine margarine, milk and sugar in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat with a spoon until of spreading consistency.

title: good baked beans
directions: Drain the tomato sauce from the 2 cans of pork and beans into a large bowl.
Add about 1 cup of brown sugar and about 1/4 cup of ketchup.
Clean and dice the green pepper and onion.
Add to sauce.
(If you don't like green peppers or hot sauce, they can be omitted.)
Add hot sauce, more ketchup and more brown sugar (to taste).
Combine this sauce with beans in a glass baking dish. Top with bacon strips or sprinkle with bacon bits.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
(If you're in a hurry, you can also cook in microwave for 10 to 15 minutes or until onions, peppers and bacon is cooked.)

title: blender chocolate pie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender for 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and pour half of mixture into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon and pour over cake mixture.
Spread remaining mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Punch holes in cake. Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.
Pour over cake while hot.

title: apricot bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; mix well.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Gradually add to butter mixture.
Add coconut, walnuts and vanilla extract; mix thoroughly.
Press 2/3 of dough into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with preserves; crumble remaining dough over preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Yields 36 bars.
Freezes well.

title: tossed sweet potato salad
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, apple, celery, walnuts, dried fruit and salt.
Blend together sour cream, mayonnaise and milk.
Fold cream mixture into potato mixture.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: spiced pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl stir together all ingredients except butter, pumpkin, buttermilk and eggs.
In medium bowl, stir together remaining ingredients.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased 12-cup muffin pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove from pan. Yield:
1 dozen.

title: asian beef and noodles
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, brown beef over medium heat until it is no longer pink, breaking up into 3/4-inch pieces.
Pour off fat and season beef with one seasoning packet from the noodles and set aside.
In same skillet, combine 2 c. water, vegetables, noodles (broken up), ginger and remaining seasoning packet.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 3 minutes or until noodles are tender, stirring occasionally.
Return beef to skillet and stir in green onions.
Makes four servings.

title: chicken glamorous
directions: Grease
pan;
cover
bottom
with
rice, then place dry onion soup
and
chicken.
Pour
soup,
which has been diluted with water,
over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° uncovered or 1 1/2 hours
at
325° for a glass dish.
Turn chicken over when half done (about 45 minutes) so it can brown.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown pepper, celery, onion, meat and salt. Simmer 5 minutes. Add soup and sauce and cook 15 minutes longer. Cook noodles and mix with meat mixture into 15 x 10 pan or roaster. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and place in a 9 x 13 pan. Heat milk, soup and cheese together. Pour over pork chops and potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovering the last 1/2 hour.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt 1/4 cup shortening in skillet and brown meatballs.
Remove balls from skillet and drain fat.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly in skillet until jelly is melted.
Add meatballs and stir until coated.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot in chafing dish.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pastry lined 9-inch pie plate.
Place into preheated hot oven, 450°, for 20 minutes. Reduce oven heat to 350°.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until a silver knife placed in the center comes out clean, as one does for a pumpkin or custard pie.
Good eating and enjoy!

title: cherry chocolate cake(makes one 9-inch cake)
directions: In medium bowl, with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and heavy cream until smooth.
Slowly add confectioners sugar, beating until smooth and creamy.

title: orange sour cream dip
directions: Combine orange juice, milk and pudding mix; beat with electric mixer until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Chill 2 hours.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Add baking powder, soda and salt to flour and sift.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Refrigerate dough for 1 hour, roll to 1/2-inch thickness, cut cookies and place on a cookie sheet.
May sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peggy boland's irish raisin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cut butter into flour; stir in raisins and caraway seed.
Combine eggs with milk and mix until you have a nice dough.
Knead for 2 minutes and shape into round loaf.
Turn into lightly greased and floured 9-inch round skillet (cast-iron is best).
Cut a deep cross on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Brush with milk when done.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat margarine until creamy, gradually adding sugar until light and fluffy.
Alternate adding flour mixture and bananas to margarine mixture, beating after each addition.
Bake in a well-greased loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken breasts for 10
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and place in plastic bag.
Add chicken and shake to cover all pieces.
Marinate overnight. Place chicken pieces on a hot grill and grill 5 minutes each side.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Mix flour and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl add all other ingredients and flour mixture.
Pour in well-greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry glazed cheesecake
directions: Combine graham crackers, walnuts, sugar and butter/margarine. Press on bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Beat eggs until light and thick; add sugar, vanilla and lemon juice while beating.
Beat in cream cheese and sour cream, a little at a time.
Beat until smooth and without lumps.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 80 minutes.
Turn off heat and leave cake in closed oven for 90 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool in pan to room temperature.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat.
Add flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon; beat.
Add zucchini, nut meats and raisins; beat.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: symphony sugar punch
directions: Gently push strawberries through sieve to remove all seeds. Pour orange juice through the strainer to remove pulp.
Make a syrup by boiling sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Mix all ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Makes 24 (16 ounce) servings.

title: brandy slush
directions: Mix 7 cups water and sugar together.
Bring to a boil.
Steep green tea bags in 2 cups water for 20 minutes.
Mix and cool.
Add orange juice, lemonade and brandy.
Serve with 7-Up or citrus soda pop.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix
together eggs, sugar and oil with electric beater. Add flour, soda and salt;
sift together.
Mix nuts and fruit in a bowl.
Add these to the batter and pour in greased mold, well floured.
Bake
1/2 hours to 2 hours at 350°.
If oven is too hot, turn back to 300° the last 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples.
Mix thoroughly and let stand while preparing batter.
Sift together flour, soda, nutmeg and salt into large mixing bowl.
Beat eggs and corn oil together.
Add to dry ingredients and continue beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, apple-sugar mixture (including juice), raisins and nuts.
Continue stirring until evenly distributed through batter.
If apples are not real juicy, add a little water.
Pour batter into well-oiled tube pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
If preferred, can add a glaze for topping, although it's delicious plain.

title: mocha coffee mix
directions: Blend all the ingredients in a medium bowl. Store in an airtight container. Makes 7 1/2 cups container. To make by the cup, put 1 tablespoon Mocha Coffee Mix in a mug and add 6 ounces boiling water; stir until mixture is dissolved.
Garnish with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pecans.
Cook in unbaked pie crust until thick and brown.

title: chateaubriand
directions: Bake larded beef tenderloin in flat, foil lined pan for 3/4 hour in a 450° oven.
Remove string and larding.
Slice and pour sauce over meat.

title: "avgolemono soupa" - egg lemon soup
directions: Add rice to boiling broth; cook unti done.
Beat the eggs until light in color; add lemon juice and mix well.
Slowly add 1 cup broth juice to eggs and beat vigorously so as not to curdle. Pour egg and broth mixture into remaining soup and mix.
Stir for about 5 minutes, so as not to curdle.
Add chopped parsley on top of soup when serving.
Serve at once.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, 1 stick oleo, 2 eggs and 1/2 teaspoon lemon extract.
Spread thick batter into slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan (with hands).
Cream 1 stick oleo and the cream cheese; blend well.
Add the powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon lemon extract and 2 eggs.
Blend well and spread over batter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown (do not overcook).

title: summer squash casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrot.
Fold in drained squash and onion.
Combine stuffing mix and butter or margarine.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown
hamburger
and	drain.	Add
envelope
of
taco seasoning according
to package directions.
Add refried beans and heat.
Pour
in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread sour cream on top
of	hamburger mixture.
Put cheese on top.	Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: pizza roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Brown sausage and drain fat. Place pizza crust on flat baking sheet.
Cut the crust down the center and roll out sides to length.
Combine sausage, pepperoni, parsley, flour, mozzarella, and mushrooms.
Place mixture on crust.
Gather crust together to form two rolls.
Mix egg white and seasoning together and brush onto crust.
Bake for 20 - 30 minutes until crust is brown.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until tender; slice as thin as possible without causing them to crumble.
Place layer of sliced potatoes in very large bowl; sprinkle with salt.
Top potatoes with layer of celery, then onions, then bacon, then parsley.
Combine mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Spread several tablespoons of dressing mixture over parsley layer.
Repeat layers several times, until all ingredients are used.
Toss salad very gently, trying not to break up potato slices more than necessary. Chill, covered, until serving time.

title: sinful mousse
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double-boiler or microwave until smooth.
Stir in rum extract; cool.
Separate 3 of the eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
In a large bowl, beat 2 remaining eggs with 3 yolks until creamy.
Stir in chocolate mixture; fold in egg whites.
Whip 1 cup cream.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into 2-quart souffle dish.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Before serving, whip remaining 1 cup of cream with vanilla and sugar. Spoon on mousse to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place corn in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Mix dry ingredients with corn and pour cream over mixture.
Cut butter into chunks and place over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Stir twice while baking.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: german upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine coconut and nuts and spread in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix by package directions.
Carefully pour this over the coconut-pecan mixture.
In a saucepan, heat the margarine and cream cheese until mixture is melted.
Stir in sugar.
Mix well and spoon over cake batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not cut until cooled.

title: tangy potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain; cool slightly.
Peel and slice potatoes; combine with onion, eggs, pickles and parsley in a large salad bowl.
Set aside.
Heat chicken broth until warm; remove from the heat.
Add mayonnaise, salt, pepper and garlic powder; mix until smooth.
Pour over potato mixture and mix lightly.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, gently stir in tomatoes and bacon.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cranberry stuffing
directions: Combine cranberries with sugar in mixing bowl.
Add bread cubes, orange peel, salt, cinnamon and butter.
Toss with enough orange juice to make mixture moist enough to hold together.
Makes enough to stuff a 9 pound turkey.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and set to cool.
Cream the cheese, sugar and vanilla; add jello a little at a time and mix well.
Whip Milnot and fold into jello mixture.
Roll crackers to make crumbs; add melted butter or oleo and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add jello mixture and sprinkle a few cracker crumbs over top for looks.
Chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine and bread crumbs.
Put in dish.
Melt margarine and milk with bread crumbs.
Top over casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Season and pour in taco sauce, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Simmer in greased casserole dish.
Layer crushed Doritos, meat filling and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: yellow rice with shrimp and scallops
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in olive oil.
When tender, add water, rice and pizza sauce.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and scallops and cook, covered, until water is absorbed.
Serve with Cuban bread and salad.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Fold in chopped eggs.
Cover with foil. Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
May be served with rice or in pastry shells.

title: corn-bread stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°F (230°C).
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and baking powder.
Stir in eggs, milk and melted butter until blended.
Spread in greased baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool. Crumble cooled corn bread.

title: sweet bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add milk, egg, flour and baking powder.
Batter will be runny.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and fat.
Spread nuts in bottom
of shell; pour in filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt margarine and saute onions.
Add cheese, soup and sour cream until smooth.
Boil potatoes, not too done. Let cool and cube into small cubes.
Mix with soup mixture.
Put in buttered casserole and top with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma lancaster's raisin cake(no eggs or milk products)
directions: Mix sugar, water, spices and Crisco; bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Mix soda and baking powder in small amount of water; pour into cooked mixture.
Add flour and nuts.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
"Old family recipe."

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
In a 12-inch skillet, brown chicken in hot oil, about 15 minutes.
Remove chicken from skillet.
In the remaining drippings, cook rice, onion and garlic. Add water, undrained tomatoes, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir well.
Arrange chicken on top of rice.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in peas and pimiento.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.

title: old-fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour and put in bottom of unbaked pastry crust. Cut small pieces of butter over sugar-flour mixture.
Pour cream over but do not mix.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes in 400° oven, then 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: association missionary's wives' pound cake
directions: Add sugar gradually to margarine.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Beat in flour, vanilla, lemon extract and almond extract.
Bake at 320° for one hour in greased and floured pan.

title: pasta, peas and prosciutto
directions: Heat oil and saute shallots and garlic for 1 minute.
Add Prosciutto; cook 5 minutes longer.
Add tomato sauce and drained peas.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and place in a large bowl.
Mix with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings.

title: chip beef dip
directions: Mix all
ingredients
(not
walnuts)
in ovenware bowl. Sprinkle with walnuts and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: nachos supreme
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet. Drain off excess grease, then add chili and heat until hot.
Place nacho chips on plate. On top of nachos, place the meat and chili mixture.
Add Cheez Whiz on top of the chili. Add the rest of the toppings, finishing off with a tablespoon of sour cream.

title: ann's appetizers
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: sausage bread
directions: Roll out dough.
Fry Italian sausage.
Put cheeses on dough; spread out, leaving 1-inch border of uncovered dough.
Add sausage.
Roll into loaf; bake by instructions on pizza dough package.

title: oatmeal milk
directions: Blend until smooth; chill and serve.

title: low country boil
directions: Boil
sausage,	onions	and
potatoes
for
20 minutes. Remove from pot
and
add	garlic	and crab boil.	Add corn to boiling water and boil 5 to 10 minutes until nearly done.
Add shrimp, sausage,
potatoes	and onions.
Boil until shrimp are done, probably not more than 5 minutes.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cover spareribs with water in a large pan.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour; drain.
Place ribs in shallow baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over ribs.
Cover; refrigerate and let marinate for 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Cover and grill ribs 5 to 6 inches from medium coals, brushing with barbecue sauce every 5 minutes until ribs are done and meat begins to pull away from bone, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: hot mushroom turnovers
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 1/2 cups of flour and 1/2 cup of butter until smooth.
Shape into ball and refrigerate 1 hour.
Saute mushrooms and onion in 3 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Stir in sour cream, salt, thyme and 2 tablespoons of flour.
Roll out dough and cut out 3-inch circles.
Put a little mushroom mixture on each; fold and brush with butter.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 450°.

title: veggies delight
directions: Melt butter on medium heat.
Add green onions, green, red and yellow bell peppers, mushrooms and bacon.
Season to taste with seasonings.
Saute until bacon is softly crisp.
Add green beans without juice.
Cover; cook for 5 minutes, then simmer until ready to serve.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place one pie crust in bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Line bottom of crust with chicken pieces.
Then add the Veg-All.
Top off with about 10 tablespoons chicken gravy. Wet rim of bottom crust and place top crust across top of pie. Seal edges.
Prick top crust.
Bake one hour at 375°.
Serve covered with gravy.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Heat butter, onion, celery salt, salt and pepper, and milk to scalding. Stir in potato buds. Continue cooking until smooth, stirring constantly. (Soup should be consistency of heavy cream.) If desired, garnish each serving with paprika and parsley. Makes 4 1-cup servings.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, carrots and celery.
Add cream of onion soup and stir together well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: potatoes and onions
directions: Cook potatoes and onions together when done sprinkle with salt and pepper, italian seasoning and butter. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Put in a buttered pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Test after 10 minutes.
Sides should be a little firm but toothpick should come out of center wet.
Cool.
Should be soft.

title: quick cheese sauce
directions: Combine in 1-quart saucepan.
Place over low heat and cook until cheese melts.
Good for sauce for broccoli.
Add 4 strips of cooked and crumbled bacon to a cup of cheese sauce for scalloped potatoes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream sugar, butter and vanilla.
Gradually add flour (the dough will be stiff).
Add pecans.
Mix with hands if necessary. Roll into finger-length cookies and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: clam chowder with bacon
directions: Fry bacon in large pan. When cooked, remove bacon. Leave some grease in pan. Add flour, diced potatoes and green onions. Saut until potatoes are browned and flour has thickened. Add milk slowly and the cream. Make sure potatoes are soft before adding clams
in juice. Simmer until clams are cooked. Do not overcook clams. Serve.

title: jerry's hillbilly beans
directions: Rinse all the beans except pork and beans. Put all ingredients in large pot. Add 2 cups water. Cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Place in hot oven at 375° for the first 10 minutes to set the crust, then reduce heat so that filling will bake but not boil.
Brown nicely.

title: finger steak
directions: Cut steak into strips, about 1 to 2-inches wide and 5 to 6-inches long.
Beat two eggs, add garlic salt.
Dip steak in mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs and deep fry.
Very good, even cold.

title: marinated coleslaw
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, turmeric, salt and pepper and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over shredded cabbage and onions and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Will keep for 3 to 4 weeks and will stay crisp.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Break up 10 biscuits into small pieces.
Soak with water until soft.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of sugar with melted 2 tablespoons of butter and eggs.
Add buttermilk, soda, 1 teaspoon vanilla and raisins (optional) and stir well.
Put in hot buttered pan.
Bake at 435° for 30 minutes.

title: linguine pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta.
While pasta is cooking, prepare the sauce. Combine soy sauce and lemon juice and whisk or blend in a blender. Combine the vegetables in a bowl.
Add soy sauce and lemon juice mixture and mix (gently).
Pour sauce/vegetable mixture over linguini.
Mix and serve.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch layer pans.
Cream margarine and shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add soda to buttermilk, then add flour and milk alternately to cake batter.
Add pecans and coconut; fold in well beaten egg whites.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken-rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook, debone and chunk chicken.
Saute broccoli and onion in margarine.
Cube the Velveeta cheese.
Cook the rice in the 2 cups of water and salt according to directions on box less 5 minutes. Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
"My family likes crushed potato chips on top."

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl and then add sour milk, egg, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Beat good and then add boiling water; beat well.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with your favorite frosting when cool.

title: potato-cheese soup
directions: In large soup pot, saute onions and garlic in butter until onions are translucent.
Add potatoes, carrots and saute for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add the stock and dill and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Puree the vegetables with the cream cheese and milk in a blender or food processor.
Return the soup to the pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and reheat gently.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: dorothy's banana bread(makes 2 big loaves.)
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda and set aside. Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, mashed bananas, honey and vanilla. Mix well. Spray pans with nonstick cooking spray. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 250°. Let set 5 minutes before taking out of pans.

title: apple pizza
directions: Arrange
apples on a pizza crust.
Sprinkle with sugar, water and
cinnamon.
Top
with crumb mixture (butter, flour, brown sugar and oats).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick and moist sour bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Add sour cream and beer alternately.
Mix well.
Pour batter into a greased 2-quart round baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes.
Brush top with butter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until tester inserted completely into center comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm, cool or toasted.
Bake at 350°.

title: fiesta dip(low-fat)
directions: Squeeze all excess moisture from the cucumbers.
Place the cucumbers in a small bowl.
Stir in the sour cream, peppers, garlic and thyme.
Transfer to a serving bowl and chill until needed.
Serve with pita wedges, low-fat crackers or crisp raw vegetables.

title: golden chews
directions: Cook oleo and brown sugar slowly until bubbly around edges. Cool.
Add eggs, vanilla, sifted flour with salt and baking powder.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Spread in shallow pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut in squares.
Will be chewy.

title: chocolate struedel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Reserve 2 cups of crumb mixture and press remainder in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: barbecued venison roast
directions: Place roast in large roasting pan.
Combine tomato sauce, water, ketchup, vinegar, hot pepper sauce, mustard, garlic and onion.
Pour sauce over roast.
Bake, covered, with aluminum foil, at 300° to 350° for 4 to 5 hours, basting periodically with sauce. Serves 12 to 16.

title: reuben casserole(microwave)
directions: Place sauerkraut in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Top with corned beef, then shredded cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and dressing; spread over cheese.
Top with tomato slices; set aside. Place butter in small glass bowl.
Microwave for about 60 seconds on Medium-high or until melted.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over tomato slices.
Microwave for 12 to 16 minutes on Medium-high or until heated through (about 150°).
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan or shape into mound and put in pie pan.
Cover with 1 1/2 strips bacon.
Cover with 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: graham ghosts
directions: Spread cream cheese on crackers; add features using raisins.

title: chocolate crunchies(no bake)
directions: Melt together peanut butter and shortening over double boiler on low heat.
Add M&M's, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add corn flakes and mix until coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Easy, quick and kids love them!

title: banana-oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour with salt, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar and egg until fluffy and light. Beat in bananas and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour mixture and oats until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: lola's sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole.

title: chocolate mocha lattice cake(3rd place in pa state greatest cocoa cake contest)
directions: Mix together the first 8 ingredients.
Beat on low and slowly add coffee, oil and vanilla.
Beat until just blended, then mix on medium for 3 minutes.
Grease 3 (8-inch) pans and dust with Hershey's unsweetened cocoa.
Pour batter evenly into prepared pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes; cool for 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Cool completely and split each layer in half.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar until sugar is mostly dissolved.
(Thin with milk if desired.)
After bacon is fried, cut into small pieces and add to the broccoli and onion.
Pour dressing over top of salad and mix until covered completely.

title: lemonade bread
directions: Put everything in bowl and beat with beaters.
Grease a loaf tin and flour.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes one loaf.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Season ground turkey to taste with salt and pepper.
Form 1-inch balls; set aside.
Combine broth, tomatoes, onion, potatoes and carrots.
Boil until potatoes are crisp-tender.
Drop meat balls in boiling stew and cook about 10 minutes.
Test meat as to doneness, then add macaroni.
Cook another 10 minutes or until pasta is tender.
Taste for seasoning.

title: mock italian meat balls i
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make walnut-size balls.
Deep fry for 5 minutes or until done.
For a loaf, you may add tomato juice or milk and bake.
Makes about 5 dozen small meat balls. Serve in or with spaghetti.

title: crab enchilada
directions: Heat olive oil; simmer garlic, onion, green pepper, oregano and bay leaves in oil.
When transparent, add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Add crabs.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large pot, brown ground meat and drain excess grease. Add taco seasoning, water, Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce, Ranch Style beans and whole kernel corn.
Stir together and bring to a boil.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Pour over Doritos chips in a bowl.

title: spaetzle(german noodles)
directions: To make dough, in a large bowl, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Blend broth, eggs and milk; add to flour mixture, beating until bubbles form, about 2 minutes.

title: grilled sirloin steak
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first 7 ingredients; add beef.
Seal bag and turn to coat.	Refrigerate for at least 3 hours or overnight.

Drain and discard the marinade. Grill steak, covered, over indirect medium heat for 1 1/2 hours, turning once, or until meat reaches desired doneness (for rare a meat thermometer should read 140°, medium 160° and well done 170°). Yield:
8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and a large onion in a pot.
Try not to put any water in the pot.
Let it steam down.
Pour into a casserole dish and top with sliced cheese.
Place cracker crumbs (Town House) on top of the cheese and put a few pats of margarine on top.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Heat skillet.
Add oil until hot.
Add vegetables and all dry seasonings.
Stir and toss until vegetables are tender.
Add soy sauce.
Cook couple more minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix jello and water.
Set aside.
Place cake mix in large mixing bowl.
Add oil and eggs (one at a time), beating well after each addition.
Add strawberries and jello mixture.
Bake in 3 (1 layer) cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice when cool.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Roll out about 1/4 inch thick. Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mock cheese souffle *
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Tear bread in pieces and pour melted margarine over it.
In blender, mix eggs, milk and seasonings. Add crumbled cheese.
Blend only until smooth.
Add bread, blend until smooth. Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350°, uncovered, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken wings and rice
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Add wings; shake to coat well.
Melt butter to sizzling in a heavy skillet.
Add green onions, celery and rice.
Stir gently until rice is golden. Add broth and thyme and stir well to blend.
Return wings to skillet; cover and simmer until done.
Top with almonds; serve hot.

title: wild rice and artichoke heart chicken salad
directions: Mix last 7 ingredients using a whisk. Set dressing aside.
Now combine all other ingredients, mixing by hand in a large bowl. Pour dressing over salad and toss until well incorporated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat all ingredients until hot.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: savory cheese bread
directions: Mix:
In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and about half the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes. Then add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour gradually until smooth.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: three minute icing
directions: Boil all ingredients together for 3 minutes, stirring enough to prevent sticking.
Remove from heat and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, flour and butter together until mix resembles pie dough.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 275° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix and chill 24 hours.
Garnish with broccoli.

title: sour cream and lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 16-cup tube or Bundt pan.
Dust pan with flour.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Brown ribs in small amount of oil and add other ingredients. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar, syrup, salt, flour and eggs.
Melt butter. Add butter, pecans and vanilla to first mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes, until filling is just set.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour into pan with margarine.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven brown beef and onion; drain. Puree the tomatoes in liquid.
Add to pan with tomato sauce, water, beans, corn and taco seasoning.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
If you desire, top each serving with avocados, cheese and serve with cheese.

title: chewy coconut raisin nut cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put small teaspoon of dough per cookie on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "brunswick stew"
directions: Stew chicken, onion, salt and pepper; save broth.
Add cabbage (cut in pieces), tomatoes and potatoes.
Take chicken off bone and cut in pieces.
Add chicken pieces, limas and corn.
Cook until all ingredients are done.

title: gourmet fudge
directions: Combine chocolate pieces, marshmallow creme, butter, nuts and vanilla.
Mix sugar and milk; heat to boiling.
Boil for 9 minutes.
Pour over chocolate mixture, stir until chocolate pieces are melted and are well blended.
Pour into buttered tins and store in the refrigerator.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onion slices in 1/2 cup beef broth and butter salt.
Add rest of beef broth and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil. Season with pepper.
Pour into bowls.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in saucepan filled with lightly salted boiling water; drain.
In a small bowl, mix together all other ingredients.
Add carrots, then place in serving dish.

title: fruit slush
directions: Heat sugar in water until dissolved. Combine bananas and enough juice in blender to mush. Combine all ingredients, except Sprite, and freeze. Serve, pouring Sprite over to make slush.

title: rice jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage; drain off fat, leaving enough to saute peppers and onions in.
Cook until tender.
Add cooked rice and other seasonings.
Heat thoroughly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: winter salad(vintersalat)
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, yogurt and pepper.
Add vegetables.
Chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Drain chili beans.
Crush Doritos.
In a large bowl, add all ingredients.
Add enough dressing to moisten and add hot sauce to taste.
(If you are not going to serve immediately, do not put the lettuce or the Doritos in until ready to serve.)

title: southern cheese salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add juices, drained pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and nuts.
Blend well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: wonderful turkey breast
directions: Combine all ingredients except turkey breast. Reserve 1 c for basting. Pour remaining marinade into a resealable 2 gallon plastic bag. Add turkey breast and seal bag. Turn to coat. Refrigerate overnight, turning several times. Drain and discard marinade. Bake 3 hr or until turkey breast is fork tender. To check with meat thermometer, it should read 185° or more. Baste frequently with reserved marinade.

title: chicken salad
directions: Steam chicken in steamer or simmer in large saucepot until fork-tender; drain and cool.
Discard skin and bones; cut meat into bite-size chunks.
In large bowl, mix chicken and remaining ingredients except chicory and tomatoes.
Chill mixture at least 1 hour to blend flavors.
To serve, line serving platter with chicory.
Spoon chicken salad onto platter and garnish with cherry tomato halves. Makes 4 main-dish servings.

title: all-star vegetable relish
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain. Combine vegetables with remaining ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
In mixer bowl, beat butter, margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Beat in flour mixture.
In small bowl, combine remaining 6 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in cinnamon-sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes per batch.
Cool on cookie sheets.
Makes about 6 dozen, 65 calories each.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and boil in salted water.
Cook until tender.
Mash potatoes.
Mix in all ingredients except marshmallows and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover top with marshmallows just before removing from oven.
Brown and serve.

title: tangy spinach l'orange
directions: In small bowl, combine oranges, onion, oil, vinegar, mustard and sugar.
Set aside.
On each Triscuits, place spinach leaf; top with teaspoonful of orange mixture.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Stir in all but 1/2 cup potato chips.
Add this 1/2 cup chips just before baking.
Make this ahead of time and refrigerate. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: coconut spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and use as a spread on toast, biscuits, cake, muffins, etc.
Can be spread on toast, then put under broiler and lightly browned.
Very good on yesterdays biscuits when they are sliced, spread and toasted in the oven.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, cream butter, shortening, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crabmeat-mushroom casserole
directions: Drain mushrooms; reserve broth.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in saucepan; blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk and mushroom broth.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mustard and tarragon.
Add mushrooms and crabmeat.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to package.
Drain noodles.
Drain tuna and mix into noodles.
Open soup and add to noodles and tuna. Pour into casserole dish.
Add milk.
Top with crackers or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° until brown (can add peas, if desired).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients in a large mixing bowl using an electric mixer.
Mix until lumps are gone and mixture is creamy.
Pour into pie crust; cover and refrigerate for 6 hours minimum.
Cut, then serve.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Blend cornmeal
with cold water.
Add to boiling water. Stir until
rapidly boiling.
Let thicken.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer 30 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust.
Mix dry jello, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil and let get thick.
Let this mixture cool, then pour over pie.
Top with fresh sliced peaches.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook the noodles and the chicken.
Cut the chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Put noodles into bottom of dish, then chicken, milk, soup and beans.
Top with bread crumbs and Velveeta cheese and bake until cheese is melted and bread is toasted.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut up fruits and mix all ingredients well!
Make a syrup from 1/2 cup sugar and 1 cup water; boil 3 minutes and pour over cake mixture.
Prepare baking pans, lining them with greased wax paper. Pour in pans; brush top with milk and bake slow at 250° for 1 hour.

title: beet cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle lemon juice over beets. Mix remaining ingredients.
Combine mixtures.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Cool, then frost with:

title: caramel candy
directions: Mix all the ingredients and cook.
Bring to boil and cook for 30 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Pour into buttered dish and refrigerate until cool, then set at room temperature.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: Break up noodles on cookie sheet; add almonds if used.
Toast 5 to 7 minutes at 350°.
In bowl, add onions, sunflower seeds and noodles to cole slaw mix.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 2 loaves in shallow baking pan.
Spread with catsup or favorite bottled barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.
Recipe may be cut in half to make one loaf.

title: hoisin turkey in lettuce cups
directions: In a large skillet, saut the ground turkey over medium-high heat, stirring, until it changes color and is cooked through. Drain well and return to pan.
Stir in cornstarch and hoisin sauce.
Heat and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Add water chestnuts and the rice and stir until heated through.

title: nana's maryland crab cakes
directions: Debone crabmeat.
Crumble 2 slices of bread and mix with crabmeat.
Add parsley, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and 1 egg.
Mix well with bread and crabmeat.
Form into 6 to 8 round balls.
Dip each ball into dried bread crumbs.
Mix 1 egg and 1/4 cup milk.
Dip crab cakes into egg and milk, rolling gently.
Dip again into bread crumbs, then deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Serve with lemon wedge.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Sift flour and sugar together. In a saucepan,
mix
butter, cocoa and water. Bring to a boil (or put in microwave for 1 minute).
Remove from heat and pour mixture over flour.
Mix well.
Add soda to buttermilk then to flour mixture.
Add
eggs
and
vanilla
and
mix.
Pour
into greased and
floured
9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour. Ice with Mississippi Fudge Cake Icing.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni or rice as usual.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Mix ground beef mixture with tomato soup and sugar.
Mix mixture with macaroni or rice.
Place croutons on top.
Then sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 15 minutes.

title: california walnut pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour in saucepan.
Add corn syrup, butter and salt; work over low heat just until butter is melted.
Beat eggs with vanilla.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Turn into pie shell; sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake on lower rack of oven at 370° for 40 to 45 minutes, until filling is set in center.
Cool before cutting.

title: easy cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute, then pour in the bottom of an angel food cake pan.
Cut biscuits in fourths; dip in melted butter, then dip in a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Drop in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Flip upside down when baked.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift together.
Mix all liquids and combine quickly with dry ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruits for 1 hour.
Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle curry and toss through fruit.
Crumble butter or margarine and brown sugar over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with curried hamburger and rice and sour cream or yogurt.

title: dodo's eggplant casserole
directions: Spray heavy saucepan with Pam.
Lightly brown onion and garlic.
Add eggplant and water or broth; cook covered until tender, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture into greased casserole.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Pour over cooked eggplant. Sprinkle with seasoning and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until cheese is melted.
Serves 4.

title: chiffon pumpkin pie(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Mix gelatine with 1/2 cup sugar, salt and spices in saucepan. Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook on low heat and stir until gelatine dissolves and thickens (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in pumpkin and chill, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg whites and remaining 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Fold stiff egg whites into pumpkin mixture and pour into baked pie crust.
Keep chilled and serve.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients to a consistency thick enough to make into patties.
Crackers may be added, if needed.
Crush approximately same amount of crackers used in mixture to roll patties in.
Have enough hot oil (deep enough to cover patties) and cook to a golden brown.

title: mushroom rice
directions: In a 2-quart microwave-safe dish, combine all ingredients. Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill.
Use to dip vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower or cucumbers.

title: pasta salad
directions: Thaw out pasta and drain.
Add meat of your choice.
Add additional salad mixture: cucumber, tomato, etc.
(optional).
Add Ranch dressing in small amounts.
Stir after each addition.
Add salt to taste.

title: breakfast loaf
directions: Cut bread in halves and butter one side.
Butter pan and arrange five slices of bread in bottom, butter side down.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Put drained broccoli on top of bread.
Cover with grated cheese; add chopped ham.
Top with other 3 slices of bread, butter side up.
Combine eggs, salt and milk.
Pour over bread.
May be refrigerated overnight or let sit at least 1 hour. Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 10 (conservatively).

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts or whole chicken in kettle with water and bay leaf until done.
Cool and cut up chicken.
Mix all ingredients together and serve on lettuce leaf or a cut circle of cantaloupe with lettuce and garnish with strawberry or orange slice on top.
Serves 4.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss cheese with flour.
Mix cheese with flour and meat and spread in pie shell.
Pour eggs, milk and seasoning mixture over meat.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles.

title: rosy glow cranberry punch
directions: In a large saucepan combine all ingredients.
Blend well. Simmer over low heat, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 24 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine condensed milk and Key lime juice, mix lightly.
Add egg yolks and cream cheese.
Blend until smooth and pour into prepared pie crust.
Mix egg whites until stiff, slowly add sugar and cream of tartar.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes or until peaks are brown.

title: grilled parmesan tomatoes
directions: Heat broiler.
Grease a baking sheet with 1 teaspoon oil. Place tomatoes in a single layer.
In a small bowl, mix remaining oil, garlic, parsley and pepper; drizzle over tomatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 5 inches from heat, about 3 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a large greased and lightly floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes one large loaf.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let thicken, then add crushed pineapple, cherries and cottage cheese.
Decorate with additional	cherries,
red and green.
Refrigerate until firm. Serve with mayonnaise.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Add box of Jiffy cornbread mix.
Bake in greased pan or muffin tins at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn cake sandwiches
directions: Melt grease in a heavy iron skillet until grease is very hot. Add part of hot grease to meal and milk mixture.
Place two tablespoonfuls of the mixture at each of the flour sides of the skillet.
Dip a spoon in water and smooth lightly over the tops of corn cakes.
Turn cakes when the bottom is browned.
Drain the cakes on paper towels, then split each one and make a heavenly sandwich, using cheese, tomatoes or corned beef with butter or mayonnaise.
Recipe should make eight corn cakes.
Watch out. Don't eat too many.

title: pepper jelly(canning)
directions: Chop or grind peppers fine.
Combine all ingredients except Certo.
Bring to boil (rolling), remove from heat, let stand 5 minutes.
Add Certo.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 3 1/2 pints.

title: laura's potato salad
directions: Lord of all pots and pans and things,

title: peach cake
directions: Mix all of these ingredients and pour in sheet cake pan and bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes or until brown.

title: feather light dumplings
directions: Sift all 4 dry ingredients together.
Add egg, melted butter and milk.
Drop by teaspoons into boiling broth and cook 18 minutes without lifting lid.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add enchilada sauce, peppers and soups.
Layer crushed Doritos, meat mixture and grated cheese twice.
Bake until heated through in 350° oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and cook about 30 to 40 minutes at 350° and top is brown.
Serves 8.

title: scarbough chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, diced.
Add Ranch Style beans, Ro-Tel chili, cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, salt, pepper and chili powder to taste.
Cook for about 15 to 20 minutes or until onion is cooked.
Place in bowls over a layer of Fritos.

title: magic cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs. Sprinkle
coconut
and chocolate chips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over
the
mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
shortening,
sugar and
eggs
together
until
it becomes light and foamy.
Mix salt, flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and oatmeal
together.
Add
raisins and nuts. Add vanilla to creamed shortening,	sugar
and eggs.
Mix well. Add all the dry ingredients to
the mixture.
Drop by teaspoons to a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for
12 to 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 16 dozen.

title: lemon cake
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and
salt	together.
Add	milk and flour alternately. Beat until
smooth.
Bake in three 9-inch cake tins.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: white sauce mix
directions: Mix together; store in refrigerator until ready to use.
When ready to use, use 2 tablespoons mix in saucepan and 1 cup liquid (makes 1 cup sauce).

title: deep dark chocolate sauce
directions: In medium size heavy saucepan, combine brown sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Mix well. Stir in water; cook over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Stir in vanilla. Serve warm.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layer cake pans.
Slice in half horizontally, after cooling.
Prepare pudding, following directions on box. Layer the ingredients in a punch bowl, starting with Cool Whip, then pudding, candy bars and cake.
Continue layering until all are used.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Enjoy.

title: stars and stripes dessert
directions: Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with 8 slices of pound cake.
Top with strawberry slices and 1 cup blueberries.
Spread thawed Cool Whip over fruit and use remaining fruit for stars and stripes design.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place first four ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil and boil hard for only one minute, but no longer.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool completely.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add rest of water and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into mold and chill.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Add cooked fresh or canned beets and 1 tablespoon butter or margarine.
Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: french apple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs; add condensed milk, apples, water, cinnamon, margarine and vanilla.
Stir in bread and raisins, completely moistening.
Turn into a buttered 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 1 hour or until firm.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Arrange in bottom of casserole.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs with butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break cooked chicken into small chunks.
Heat soup.
Mix chicken and all ingredients except stuffing into soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish and cover with 1/4 inch of stuffing.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Heat juice from cherries to dissolve jello. Add rest of ingredients.
Chill and serve in squares.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat together. Mix together flour and nuts; add to mixture.
Chill several hours.
Form 1-inch oblong rolls (approximately 4). Cut in round disks.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: tammy's potato soup
directions: Bring 8 cups water to a boil in a Dutch oven.
Dice potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes and add to boiling water.
Add salt, butter and garlic powder.
Cook potatoes until tender.
Add milk and cheese.
Use potato masher and mash while hot.
This will thicken mixture.
Serve garnished with parsley flakes.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, combine margarine, peanut butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat.
Add flour mix.
Stir in 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Spread mix in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread remaining chips over top, spreading until all melted.
Cool and cut; serve.

title: spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a large shallow baking dish or skillet.
Combine water and milk.
Heat to simmer.
Add the corn meal, salt, sugar and butter and stir over medium heat until the mixture is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Remove from the heat. Beat the eggs with the baking powder until very light and fluffy. Then add them to the corn meal mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into the prepared dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: german slaw
directions: Heat cup of vinegar with 7/8 cup sugar until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Pour 3/4 cup oil over cabbage, onion, green pepper, sugar, salt, celery and mustard; mix well.
Stir in vinegar/sugar dressing; mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a lightly greased 2-quart casserole, combine milk, rice, sugar and salt.
Bake, uncovered, for two hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
Add raisins during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Stir in surface crust.
Upon standing, rice will absorb milk remaining in casserole.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: gladys weaver tater tot casserole
directions: Cook hamburg.
Mix soup with 1 can of milk.
Combine with hamburg.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sliced cheese and Tater Tots.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: mom's lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute meats and drain grease.
Add tomatoes and sauce to meats; keep separate.
Beat eggs, cottage cheese, parsley and salt and pepper to taste.

Layer to these directions: (1) place a skimpy layer of meat on bottom of glass dish (a large rectangular dish is best); (2) place 3 strips of noodles onto this; (3) place 1/2 cottage cheese mixture on top of noodles; (4) place Mozzarella cheese over entire area; (5) place another layer of meat; (6) place another layer of noodles; (7) add cottage cheese mixture; (8) place another layer of Mozzarella cheese; (9) another layer of meat and (10) sprinkle Parmesan cheese over. Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Let set up 45 minutes before serving.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix together the rice and broccoli; place in a greased casserole dish.
Top with the chicken.
Combine the can of mushroom soup, 1 can of broth from cooking the chicken, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry to taste (1 tablespoon at least).
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Can be made ahead of time, refrigerated and then cooked.

title: meaty cheese dip
directions: Cook ground beef and sausage until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add Lipton soup mix and 2 cans Ro-Tel.
Stir.
Cut cheese in chunks. Add to meat mixture.
Cook on medium-low heat until cheese melted. Serve with choice of chips or corn chips.

title: beef brisket
directions: In large roaster, put beef brisket, potatoes and carrots. Cover brisket with ketchup and pour vermouth over top of ketchup. Bake at 350° until soft, about 20 minutes per pound.

title: homemade hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: almond skillet coffee cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour batter into 9-inch iron skillet which has been lined with aluminum foil, shiny side up.
Cover top with almonds and sprinkle on sugar.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
May take longer in some ovens, cake should be light brown.
Remove cake from pan when it cools and peel off foil.
Do not remove foil while it is hot.
Wrap tightly to store.
Freezes well.
Recipe from Billy Joe Brown at Christian Women's Club breakfast.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and flour; beat and add fruit and nuts.
Spread 1 inch thick.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Cream together all ingredients except chocolate.
Pat into large greased rectangular baking pan or a cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° or until light brown.
Remove from oven and cover with 6 to 8 Hershey bars or a layer of chocolate chips.
Spread chocolate as it melts.
Cut while still warm and soft (into bars). Refrigerate.
Very rich!

title: great and easy soup
directions: Brown and drain meat and onions.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir and heat well.

title: barbecued stew beef
directions: Place stew beef into baking dish.
After mixing the first 7 ingredients, pour over the meat and cover with metal foil.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: green salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Slice 3 boiled eggs over top.

title: broccoli and carrot stir-fry
directions: In wok or large skillet, heat the oil briefly.
If using fresh garlic and/or ginger, add and stir-fry for 15 seconds.
Add the broccoli, carrots and onions, tossing the vegetables to mix them well.
Add the water, cover and cook for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Remove cover and turn the heat to high.
Cook the vegetables, stirring them 5 minutes longer or until the vegetables are tender-crisp.
If using garlic powder or ground ginger, add and mix in soy sauce.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour syrup into saucepan; boil rapidly, uncovered, for 5 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cream the sugar, butter, salt and flour.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla; mix well.
Sprinkle nuts into mixture in unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, or until pie is completely puffed across top.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well and keep covered in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Prepare the night before or at least 5 to 6 hours before.

title: dilly bread
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add salt, dill weed, onion, 4 tablespoons sugar, dill seed and cottage cheese.
Heat and stir until lukewarm.
Meanwhile, in 1/2 cup water, add 1/2 teaspoon sugar, ginger and yeast.
When this gets bubbly and begins to rise, pour first mixture into large bowl and add soda, then add yeast mixture, eggs and cheese.
Add flour; beat well.
Cover with wax paper.
Set in warm place to rise until doubled, approximately 30 minutes.
Beat down and scrape out on well floured board.
Knead slightly.
Cut into 6 equal parts.
Form each into balls.
Set on 2 greased cookie sheets.
Let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Switch pans.
Place foil on top of each.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes. Butter tops.
Cool on rack.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift 2 cups flour with soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Dice orange slice candy.
Mix with 1/2 cup flour and add candy mixture to first mixture.
Stir in coconut, chopped nuts and oats.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: divinity
directions: Boil the sugar, water and salt 2 minutes.
In mixing bowl, put the marshmallow cream and pour hot syrup over this and beat until thick enough to drop on wax paper; beat with spoon.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish.
Cover with bacon.
Bake at 350° until bacon is done.

title: gourmet spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large salad bowl.
Add seasonings, then dressing and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: german potato pancakes
directions: Mix all together; stir well.
Fry slowly until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk. Stir in bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper. Add beef to mixture and mix well. Put in loaf pan or casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Pour off excess fat. Combine ketchup, sugar and mustard and spread over loaf. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Boil together first 4 ingredients for about 5 minutes; remove from stove and let cool.
Add gumdrops, cut in small pieces.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti, chicken, pepper and parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: country baked pork chops
directions: Wash roast in vinegar water and drain.
In crock-pot, place roast and sprinkle 1 package of onion soup mix. Cook on low overnight.

title: sweet and sour goulash
directions: Brown meat in oil and add all ingredients, except cornstarch. Cover and cook 3 hours (simmer).
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Pour goulash over noodles.

title: super slo-cooker supper
directions: Combine all but the rice in a slo-cooker.
Bring to a boil on high heat, then reduce heat and slo-cook for 4 hours.
Remove the chicken and discard the skin and bones.
Measure the remaining liquid and, if necessary, add enough more bouillon to make 2 1/2 cups.
Return chicken, liquid and rice to slo-cooker; slo-cook an additional 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pickle sticks
directions: Cut cucumbers and pour boiling water over them.
Let stand for 5 to 6 hours.
Mix ingredients in saucepan and boil 5 minutes. Pour over cucumbers that are packed tight in cans.
Boil in cans for 5 minutes to seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: rice goulash(home favorite of mary sue and bruce lambert)
directions: Chop in large bite size pieces the green peppers, onions, sweet red pepper and mushrooms.
Chop the celery in small pieces. Cook all the vegetables in large deep skillet.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked but still crunchy.
(You may need to add a little tomato paste to thicken if desired.)
Serve over rice. Shredded cheese topping adds to the dish.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Place meat in a long, shallow pan.
Cover with liquid smoke and sprinkle generously with garlic salt, onion salt and celery salt. Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle generously with Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake at 275° for 5 hours (drain).
Combine remaining ingredients to make barbecue sauce and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Cover brisket with barbecue sauce and bake 1 more hour at 325° to 350°.
Cool before slicing.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream egg, butter, sugar and vanilla; stir in salt and flour. Pat in rectangle on greased baking sheet, leaving 1 inch around edge.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread chocolate bars on top while hot.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Prepare and microwave crust as directed.
Set aside.
Place cream cheese in medium mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cream cheese softens.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer until blended.
Set aside.
Place chocolate in small bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until chocolate can be stirred smooth 1 or 2 times.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Add sour cream.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust.
Place on inverted saucer in microwave.
Microwave on High 12 to 15 minutes or until center is slightly set, rotating pie plate every 3 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Chill for 6 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 stick margarine with the Velveeta cheese.
Melt together and mix with thawed, drained broccoli.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Spread on top of broccoli.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and golden on top (approximately 25 minutes).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli into flowerets.
Cut onions into thin rings. Combine onions and broccoli pieces and add sunflower seeds and raisins.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Bake ribs in a 250° oven 3 hours. Add sauce and bake another 1 1/2 hours.
Grill on top of tinfoil that is sprayed with Pam.

title: corn muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine both mixes.
Add the required ingredients (eggs, milk, water, etc.) as each package directs.
Mix well by hand or electric mixer.
Pour into muffin pans and bake as package directions indicate.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients until smooth.
Mix brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour hot water over top of sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not overbake. Serve warm or cold upside down.

title: herbed corn-on-the-cob
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, salt, pepper, parsley, and rosemary in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Cut six 12 inch pieces of heavy-duty foil.
Spread appr. 1 Tbsp. butter mixture onto each ear of corn, reserving remaining butter mixture.
Place one ear of corn diagonally on each piece of foil.
Roll up tightly.
Twist ends to seal.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake corn for 30 minutes. Untwist the ends of foil and unroll.
If desired, fold the edges of foil up around each ear of corn to form a "boat".
Top corn with a small amount of remaining butter mixture.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: (Ingredients can be increased or decreased to fit your family.) In roasting pan or large flat 9 x 13-inch casserole, put rice, vegetables and mushrooms pieces with water from can and can of chicken broth.
Place chicken breasts on top.
(I use boneless or boned.)
Spice with Italian seasonings or whatever you like.
(This is a great, quick dinner.)
Cook covered for 30 minutes at 375°, then uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Water may need to be added for rice.

title: macaroni oven dinner
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Rinse in cold water.
Cook celery, onion, tomatoes, green pepper and seasoning together 30 minutes.
Combine drained macaroni, vegetables, seasonings, meat, parsley and 3/4 cup grated cheese. Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven 325° for 1 hour.
Top with 1/4 cup cheese last 5 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute.
Add sugar and shortening and beat 1 minute.
Add vanilla and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and combine with first mixture.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° or 375° until they look done (ovens vary), 8 to 10 minutes. Ice tops when cool (optional).

title: cheddar chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken 25 minutes.
Drain broth and save.
Cool chicken; tear into chunks.
Cook macaroni in water.
Drain. Place macaroni in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Cover with chicken.
Thin soup with broth, 2/3 cup with each can of soup.
Pour soup over top of chicken.
Top with crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until they start to get tender.
Drain and return to pan.
Add cheese, soup and sausage.
Pour into a Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Pour in 1/4 to 1/2 cup of milk.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicago homemade dill pickles
directions: You will need 1 (1-gallon) glass jar (a "sun-tea" glass beverage server is ideal too!).

title: applenut cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: vegetable almondine
directions: Saute celery in oil until soft; add corn, mushrooms and almonds.
Saute for 3 minutes and add rest of ingredients.
Serve hot.

title: french mint tea
directions: Boil lemon rinds with 6 cups water and 2 cups sugar for 5 minutes.
Remove lemon rinds.
