Add vanilla, almond flavoring and lemon
juice.
Steep
regular
size
tea
bags
in 4 cups boiling water
for 3 to 5 minutes.	Add tea to other ingredients and last add the unsweetened pineapple juice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into greased casserole. Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of butter and graham crackers.
Pat into a 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
In an electric mixer, mix eggs, remaining butter and powder sugar.
Beat together no less than 15 minutes.
Spread mixture over graham cracker crust and cover with a single layer of spiced bananas.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with walnuts and cut up cherries.
Best when refrigerated overnight.
Serves 12.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: In a 1 quart serving bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine sliced apples, caramel topping and flour in a bowl.
Spoon into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Peel apart each biscuit into 2 thinner biscuits and place on top of apples. Combine melted butter, brown sugar and chopped nuts. Spread over biscuits. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: french lemon pie
directions: Whip eggs.
Add sugar, salt, flour, oleo and Karo syrup and mix well.
Add lemon
juice.
Pour	into
an
uncooked pie shell. Let set 10	minutes.
Bake	in 400° oven approximately 45 minutes or until it shakes like jello.

title: mysteries(recipe from nana, codie smith's mother)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cut into square bars and roll in powdered sugar.

title: stella d'oro cream puffs
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix softened cream cheese with Cool Whip for about 2 minutes or until well mixed.
Add pineapple; mix thoroughly.
Cut cookies in half horizontally; spoon about 1 tablespoon of mixture on bottom half.
Replace top. Refrigerate.
Makes 20 to 24 cream puffs.

title: john's school wheaties cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, coconut, Wheaties and leavening agents.
Make walnut-size balls. Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350°
for 6 minutes, or golden brown on a greased pan.

title: jalapeno corn bread salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, except you can save some of the cheese, tomatoes and bacon to sprinkle on top.
Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and Tabasco sauce together.
Combine everything together well and chill.
This does not mold.

title: peanut butter hot fudge sauce
directions: Put chocolate bits and milk in heavy one-quart saucepan and heat until chocolate is melted, stirring constantly.
Add peanut butter and stir until blended.
Makes 1 1/2 cups; may be refrigerated.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt
margarine; add
chips
and
peanut
butter.
Melt stuff again.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla flavoring; pour over 9 cups of Rice Chex or
Crispix.
Stir
well.
Put 1 1/2 cups of powdered sugar in a
gallon
plastic
bag. Put in Chex mixture and shake, then eat.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Saute all vegetables in garlic until tender.
Cook pasta. Over low heat cook 1 quart light cream.
When thickening begins, add spices and lightly scrambled egg.
Add Parmesan cheese until very thick.
Pour over pasta.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Mix the last 4 ingredients. Place the first mixture into casserole.
Add the last 4 ingredient mixture, sprinkling over the top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; reserve 1/4 cup.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas to first Jell-O mixture.
Pour into rectangular dish; refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine cookie crumbs and butter; pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring pan. In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add condensed milk; beat until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. In a small bowl, toss together 1/2 cup chips with flour until the chips are coated; stir into cheese mixture. Pour into prepared 9-inch pan. Sprinkle remaining chips evenly on top. Bake for 1 hour. Cake should spring back when touched lightly---then it's done!! Cool at room temperature. Keep in pan until you serve. Refrigerate later.

title: ricotta pie
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour, 3 egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and the butter; mix into a dough.
Form into a ball.
Cover with plastic and let rest in the refrigerator.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: Mix the eggs, butter and sugar in double boiler for 1/2 hour. Cool.
Add	to
graham crackers, marshmallows and nuts. Spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.	Top with chocolate chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the sugar, milk, and butter; cook on medium-high heat until mixture comes to full boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the remaining ingredients. Mix until smooth and pour into 9 inch square buttered pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with a mixer.
Spread mixture in the bottom of a pie plate.
Spread chopped pepper, onion and jalapenos on top.
Pour pizza sauce on top and top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: When mixed well, add 3/4 cup pecan halves.
Pour the complete mixture into a 9-inch pastry-lined pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a 375°
oven just until set.
Serve slightly warm (good cold, also) and garnished with ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: texas beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Mix other ingredients and add to hamburger.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 45 minutes.

title: delicious butter pop-ups
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° in muffin pans for 20 minutes. Don't overcook.
Makes 12.
These are wonderful!

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time to the butter and sugar mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring.
After all ingredients are mixed, beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: country style vanilla ice cream
directions: In a
large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar;
beat
until
thickened.
Add cream, half and half, vanilla and salt and mix thoroughly.
Pour into can; add milk to line
on
can
and	stir well.
Follow your ice cream maker's instructions for proper freeze.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: meatballs - low-fat
directions: Mix well and bake on cookie sheet at 350° until done.
Yields about 23 meatballs.
One meatball equals 1 gram fat, 40 calories.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut all biscuits into quarters.
Place 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in a brown bag.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time, and shake until coated. Arrange coated pieces in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Place the remaining sugars, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and margarine in a saucepan. Bring to a boil. Pour over the biscuits.
Place in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Piece off with toothpicks or fingers.
You may add chopped pecans, if you desire.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use chicken broth if needed.
Chop giblets and chicken very fine.
Bake in greased 15 x 18-inch pan in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp or crawfish opelousas
directions: Mix all ingredients in rice cooker.
Cover.
Do not open until bell rings.
Enjoy!!!!

title: another christmas cookie(cut-outs)
directions: Cream well the oleo, white sugar, salt, egg and baking powder. Add coffee cream or half and half and flour.
Roll out and cut in desired shapes.
Frost or whatever.

title: best peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese together.
Add powdered sugar and milk.
Lightly fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in crust and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: rice dressing
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all other ingredients, except green onion tops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or simmer 1/2 hour on stove top.
Add green onion and adjust seasonings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix soup until smooth; stir in Milnot.
Add tuna, peas and pimiento; blend slightly.
Place 3/4 cup of chips in bottom of baking dish.
Pour over tuna mixture.
Top with remaining potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese pate
directions: Combine all ingredients, except parsley.
Put on waxed paper and shape into log.
Roll in parsley. Chill.
Freezes well.

title: coffee can cake
directions: I use a potato masher to mash bananas until liquid
and use it to continue stirring in all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°. Butter and flour 4-1 lb. coffee (metal) cans.
Pour equally into the 4 cans.
Bake approximately 1 hour or until brown and done on top.

title: joyce's  broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli. Mix all ingredients together, except crackers. Pour into a baking dish and cover with Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bread crumbs and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Spread the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix the bread crumbs into 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Sprinkle over the casserole. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: chili soup surprise
directions: Cook rice separately in 2 cups of water.
Brown meat and onion together in a large soup pot.
Drain off grease.
Add cooked rice, vegetable juice, kidney beans, carrots, tomatoes, chili powder, pepper and garlic to meat and onions in a large pot.
Bring to boil.
Serve.
Makes a meal for 6 people.
Goes well with cornbread.

title: smoky pasta and bean soup
directions: In a large skillet, saute bacon until some fat is rendered. Add onion, celery, carrot, garlic, and red pepper.
Saute until vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook another 10 minutes.
Stir in beans, add broth, and bring to a gentle boil.
Add pasta and cook gently until pasta is tender, but firm.
Serve immediately with Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in ketchup and tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place cheese over beef mixture.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's caramel corn
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add the soda and vanilla.
Pop approximately 2 gallons popcorn. Cover popcorn with syrup mixture.
Bake on 2 cookie sheets at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: jam and cheese loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water; stir in Bisquick mix, egg and the 1 tablespoon of sugar; mix well.
Turn onto surface dusted with additional Bisquick mix.
Knead gently for 20 strokes. Place dough on center of a greased 15 1/2 x 12-inch baking sheet. Roll to 14 x 9-inches.

title: pepperoni and cheese appetizer bread
directions: Measure warm water into a large bowl; sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until double.

title: stromboli
directions: Tear one bread loaf into four pieces (make four out of one loaf).
Make each piece into a round pizza shell.
Top each with Provolone cheese slices, boiled ham, pepperoni, cut up onions and mushrooms and chopped sweet peppers.
Top with shredded Mozzarella. Put a little sauce over all, fold over and seal.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pot pie
directions: Cut the lard into combined dry ingredients.
Stir in lightly beaten egg and water.
On floured board, roll out as thinly as possible.
Cut into 2-inch squares and cook in chicken, ham or beef broth.
Add an onion, 4 potatoes (sliced) and minced parsley.
Stir with a fork so pot pie does not stick together and cook for about 20 minutes.
If too dry, add boiling water to broth.

title: chicken salad from the lazarus chintz room
directions: Serve on lettuce leaf with fresh fruit at side of plate. Serve with muffins, banana bread, etc.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Combine butter, flour and pecans; mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.

title: tuna specials
directions: Chop the sweet pickles, olives, green peppers and eggs.
Dice the Velveeta cheese.
Mix the ingredients together with approximately 1 cup of mayonnaise (more or less, depending on your liking).

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in medium bowl.
In small bowl mix peanut butter, milk, egg, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add first mixture until all flour is moistened.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Drain pineapple and add.
Add marshmallows; mix well and chill.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put all ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Last 10 minutes, add 2 beaten eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out on cutting board.
Cut into long strips; let dry.

title: spanish corn
directions: Line buttered casserole with corn. Layer half of all the other ingredients and then repeat.
Dot with butter. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy crab bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Serve over rice or pasta.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: pasta and olives
directions: *Can use tomato, green pepper, broccoli, mushrooms, onions and red pepper.

title: chicken breasts tarragon
directions: In large Dutch oven, heat 2 tablespoons oil and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add 1/2 of chicken breasts and saute until brown on all sides.
Remove.
Brown remainder of chicken.
Remove from pan.
To drippings, add onion and carrot.
Saute, stirring, 5 minutes, or until golden.
Return chicken to pan.
Heat.
Heat cognac in ladle over gas flame or electric burner.
Ignite cognac with match. Pour flaming cognac over chicken.
Add wine, tarragon, chervil, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer gently, covered, 30 minutes.
Remove chicken to heated platter. Keep warm.
Strain drippings, reserving veggies in a warm place. Return drippings to pan. In small bowl, combine cream, yolk and flour.
Mix well with whisk.
Stir into drippings in pan.
Bring just to boiling.
Add more wine if sauce seems too thick.

title: nacho dip
directions: Cook onions in margarine over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cheese melts.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: easy rice almond pilaf
directions: In skillet, combine margarine and almonds. Saute until almonds are slightly brown.
To this, add the remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to
a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer, cover and continue cooking for 20 minutes or until all water is absorbed. Fluff with a fork.

title: fruit salad
directions: Toss bananas and apple in orange juice.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: stone soup
directions: In a large pot combine beef, water, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; add the barley, celery, carrots, onions and potatoes.
Simmer for two hours.
After two hours stir in the milk and serve with bread.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 cup sugar and the corn syrup.
Blend in bourbon.
Combine crumbs and nuts,
add chocolate mixture and blend well.
Shape quickly into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Store in airtight container and let stand several days to ripen before serving. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: baked beans with maple syrup
directions: Wash and pick over beans. Cover with cold water. Add soda and soak for 8 hours or overnight. Rinse beans and boil in fresh water until skins wrinkle, 8 to 10 minutes. Drain off bean water and set aside. Place whole onion in bottom of bean pot or 3-quart baking casserole dish with lid. Add beans, syrup, salt and mustard. Stir to coat. Cover beans with the bean water. Bake for 6 to 7 hours in a 300° to 325° oven. Check and add water as needed.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake mix by box directions; crumble in a punch bowl.

title: cream cheese pound cake(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour 4 times and add gradually. Mix well with vanilla and lemon flavoring. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°. Check and leave longer if needed.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Can also be baked in a Bundt pan.

title: kahlua layered dessert
directions: Bake cake mix as instructed. In a large mixing bowl, break up the cake mix after it has cooled. Pour Kahlua over the cake until cake is very moist and crumbly. Mix Cool Whip with powdered sugar (about a cup). Prepare pudding as instructed.

title: coal miners delight
directions: Crush Oreos and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour over Oreos.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: eggs strata
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
In same pan, melt butter; brown hash browns.
In 2-quart dish, layer sausage, potatoes and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and salt; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Serves 8.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to creamed mixture. Chill until cold all the way through. Roll out on floured pastry cloth or pastry board and cut any shape you want to. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Even better if you let them marinate for 2 to 3 days.

title: pumpkin ham soup
directions: Clean the pumpkin; remove seeds.
Cut the pumpkin into small pieces.
Saute the onions and garlic in the peanut oil, add to the 8 quarts of chicken stock; add the pumpkin, hot diced peppers and ham.
When the pumpkin is tender, mash or puree.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes more.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: In 4-quart pan put beans and onion and salt into 2-quarts of water.
Put in ham or bacon, stirring occasionally.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Pour milk into large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat for 30 seconds. Add lemonade concentrate. Beat 30 seconds more; will be thick. Immediately stir in whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Store leftover in the refrigerator.

title: felix's french toast
directions: Heat griddle.
Combine eggs, milk and cinnamon in a deep dish and beat until smooth.
After griddle is heated, open and put a little butter (or margarine) and spread around on griddle.
Dip bread slices into batter and put on griddle.
Cook a couple of minutes
on each side of bread until golden brown.
Take off griddle and add butter or margarine and syrup or fruit to your liking.

title: tangy cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans; mix well. Chill at least 1 hour. Roll in pecans.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Mix flour and soda. Add to shortening.
Mix alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat 25 minutes at 350°.
Put in 2 or 3 (9-inch) pans.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil; cool.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt in a large mixing bowl. Add cooled cocoa mixture to dry ingredients.
Beat the eggs, sour cream and vanilla into batter.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cubes; stir.
Add lemon juice, crushed pineapple and grated carrots.
Chill slightly.
Fold in pecans and finish chilling.
Enjoy!

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Chop all of the vegetables fine.
Pour 1 cup sugar on top, then set aside.
Boil 1 tablespoon sugar, salt, salad oil, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Set in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Will keep for several days.

title: crispy potato wedge
directions: Place potatoes in a large bowl; add cold water to cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.
Drain potatoes.
Dry potatoes, using paper towels.
Place in a large bowl and sprinkle with oil, salt and pepper.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes. Turn potatoes and sprinkle with garlic.
Bake 20 more minutes.

title: good cajun biscuits
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Gradually pour in club soda; mix lightly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.
Brush with oleo halfway through cooking and also after biscuits are done.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Bring water, sugar, salt and cream of tartar to a boil.
Add crackers and set off heat.
Add a lump of butter and some cinnamon.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Add whipped topping.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: In a
greased
x
12-inch
dish,
combine
first two ingredients and 1 cup of cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk. Pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: cranapple casserole
directions: Roll diced apples and cranberries in sugar.
Place in greased baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and sprinkle over apples and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be made ahead.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together first 6 ingredients. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream or cake.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: potato pot
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel and coarsely shred.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and oleo, stirring occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, mixing lightly, and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Bake for 25 minutes or until heated through in preheated 350° oven.

title: meringue
directions: Put first four ingredients into a small mixing bowl and beat until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff but not dry.
Add vanilla. Spread on top of pie filling, being careful to spread to crust and seal edges. Bake at 350° until meringue is a golden brown.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: With mixer blend all ingredients but crab. Drain crab.
Break up and add to mixture with spoon.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled with crackers, vegetables or chips.

title: broccoli salad #2
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-sized flowerets.
Steam 2 minutes in the microwave; drain.
Place broccoli in a salad bowl.
Add the sliced olives, chopped eggs, green onions and bacon.
Combine salad dressing, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Just before serving, pour over broccoli salad and toss.
This becomes a meal with the addition of stir-fried chicken.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar into heavy iron skillet and heat slowly, stirring constantly, just until sugar is melted and turns a light brown (300° plus).
Butter baking pan or cookie sheet.
Spread peanuts over surface, sprinkle with salt, then warm tin slightly.
Pour melted sugar over peanuts.
When cool, break into pieces and store in tightly covered container.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until ground beef is brown and onions tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomato, beans, rice, water, green pepper, chili powder, salt and garlic salt.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top meat mixture with shredded cheese.
Cover and heat about 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle corn chips around edges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandiose nachos
directions: Fry meat until browned, breaking up with fork into little pieces, then drain.
Mound each tortilla chip with meat, tomato, onion and cheese in that order.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour (a little at a time).
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Set beets aside.
Boil 1 dozen eggs and peel when cool.
Set aside.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine and mix well.
Makes 25 (1/2-cup) measures.

title: sugar creek chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine butter and sugar in a saucepan over medium heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth. Remove from heat.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Stir in vinegar, vanilla and salt.
Beat to blend and pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake 50 minutes or until it tests done.

title: pound cake(makes two 9 x 5-inch loaves)
directions: Cream margarine until light.
Cream in sugar and beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat in 1 cup of flour, alternating with ginger ale, until all ingredients are used.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans or one 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 275° oven for one hour and 45 minutes, or until knife or cake tester inserted in middle of cake comes out clean and cake has begun to shrink from sides of pan. Let cool in pan.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Rinse potatoes and dry.
Brush 1 tablespoon margarine on bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of cheese.
Toss potatoes with remaining margarine.
Layer 1/3 potatoes on bottom of pie plate; sprinkle with 1/3 of cheese; salt, pepper and garlic powder as desired.
Repeat with 2 more layers.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and lightly browned.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Saute seafood and shallots in 4 tablespoons butter for about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with 6 tablespoons sherry, salt and pepper.
In a pan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk and remaining sherry.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top. Bake 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: pinto bean pot
directions: Wash beans and place in a large pot.
Add water.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 2 hours.
Drain and rise.
Add fresh water to cover.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt and then hocks.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Remove skin and bones from hocks.
Return meat to a pot.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon of salt and rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, until done.

title: saucy sausage skillet
directions: In large skillet, saute sausage and garlic over medium-high heat for 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and onion; cook another 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes with juice, basil, oregano and bouillon cube, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Add zucchini; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally.
Cook 15 minutes, until zucchini is tender.
Toss with twist trio.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: mom's custard
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, salt, vanilla and mix well.
Add to scalded milk.
Bake in Corning casserole uncovered 10 minutes at 400°
and 25 minutes at 325°.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: While browning ground beef in a pan, mix other ingredients in crock-pot.
Add browned beef and cook on high for a while, then turn on low.

title: white trash
directions: In saucepan, melt chocolate and oil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
In a large bowl, pour mixture over cereal, gently tossing until well coated.
Place sugar in small trash bag.
Add coated cereal and close bag tightly.
Shake bag gently until cereal is thoroughly coated
with sugar (may need more than 2 cups).
Keep in airtight container.

title: honeybun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Put 1/2 of batter in oblong pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top of batter; add the other 1/2 of batter.
Swirl top.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Hand beat eggs; mix rest of ingredients with eggs.
Bake in Bundt pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: sherry chicken a la king
directions: Mix together chicken, sherry and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, saute mushrooms and margarine until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until bubbly.
Add milk, broth and soup, slowly stirring until mixed well.
Add chicken mixture and pepper to taste.
Heat through and serve over rice or noodles. Tastes best over pastry shells.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese, salt, vanilla, evaporated milk and coconut.
Form into big ball and chill for 15 minutes.
Roll into small balls using your hands and then roll to coat in cinnamon.
Makes about 100 candies.

title: creamy cabbage slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and pour over shredded cabbage. Chill before serving.

title: sue's sweet and sour meatballs
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except meatballs. Mix thoroughly. Place meatballs in the bottom of a 13 x 13 casserole dish; pour mixture over meatballs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter and Sugar Twin.
Add egg, vanilla, nonfat milk and water; beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Fold in chocolate candy.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Add mayonnaise for consistency. Serve with crackers.

title: christmas rice
directions: Put all ingredients in baking dish.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Stir about 3 times while cooking.

title: cheesy chicken enchiladas
directions: In a medium saucepan combine salsa and cheese.
Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until cheese melts.
Set aside 1 1/4 cups sauce.
Stir chicken into remaining sauce.
Spoon some of the chicken mixture down the center of each tortilla.
Place filled tortillas, seam side down, in a greased baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: apple jonathan
directions: In bowl, toss apples and syrup until apples are coated. Spread apples in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Mix sugar, butter and beaten egg.
Stir in flour, orange peel and orange juice.
Spread batter over hot apples. Return to oven.
Bake 30 minutes more, uncovered.

title: french creme cookies
directions: Cream shortening and powdered sugar, then add vanilla and beaten egg until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes at 350°.

title: jelled salad supreme
directions: Dissolve the raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.

Stir in pie filling. Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill until firm. Dissolve the lemon gelatin in remaining 1 cup boiling water; cool. Beat cheese with mayonnaise until blended and smooth. Gradually add lemon gelatin.
Stir in pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until partly set. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon over cherry layer. Top with pecans.
Chill until set.

title: layered lemon crumb bars(makes 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In small mixing bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and rind; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour, oats, baking powder and salt; mix until crumbly.
Spread half the oat mixture into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Press down firmly.

title: lob-la-la casserole
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in small amount of oil; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into casserole and bake at 300° to 350° for 30 minutes.
Very good to take camping.

title: raspberry truffles
directions: In 1-quart glass measure, combine 10 ounces chocolate and butter.
Heat in a microwave oven on High until melted and smooth when stirred.
Stir in jam and liquor until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours, or overnight.

title: dough(for use in pizza and fried filled dough.)
directions: Combine yeast, water
and
sugar
together.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Place flour and salt in large bowl.
Stir
in
yeast
mixture and slightly cooled potatoes.
Mix until a smooth, soft dough forms.
Knead on floured surface, using as much
as
cup
of
flour,
if needed. Knead dough for
minutes,
until
a
silky
dough appears. Let dough rise in covered greased bowl in warm place until double in size, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone.
Shred chicken and put into a pot. Add soups and one block of grated cheese.
On low heat, mix until cheese is melted and mixed together.
Put half of the mixture into tortillas and roll up like an enchilada.
Place into a pan and put the rest of the mixture on top of the enchiladas.
Add the other block of cheese to the top.
Place in oven on low heat until cheese is melted.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach, remove stems, and tear leaves into small pieces.
Add feta cheese and grapefruit.
Mix.
Stir in dressing just before serving.

title: cousin ann's black-eyed pea dip
directions: Marinate overnight.
May add cayenne pepper.
Serve with Fritos Scoops.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together well; mash.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake for an additional 5 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add mashed banana, partially thawed frozen strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour half of the mixture and let set.
Spread on sour cream and cheese which have been blended.
Pour on remainder of jello and fruit.

title: pot roast with wine
directions: Preheat oven to slow (250°).
Sprinkle the roast with salt and pepper.
Heat the oil in a Dutch oven or other heavy roaster and brown the meat lightly on all sides.
Add the garlic, onions, celery, seasonings and wine; cover.
Bake 6 to 8 hours or until the meat is thoroughly tender.
Remove the bay leaf and allspice. Put the gravy through a sieve, or puree it in a blender.
Serve with the sliced meat.

title: hot spud salad
directions: Mix everything together, except for olives and place in baking dish.
Put olives on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: enchilada
directions: Dip taco shells in gravy and enchilada sauce.
Fill with hamburger, beans, sour cream and cheese.
Fold over and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover pan with foil and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Add flavorings.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: coffee kanten
directions: Dissolve together cool coffee with gelatin.
Add hot coffee. Add tsubushi and condensed milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill.

title: pumpkin-brandy cheesecake
directions: Combine gingersnap crumbs, 1/3 cup almonds and cinnamon, mixing well.
Add butter and stir well.
Press evenly onto bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Cool crust completely on a wire rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In greased shallow casserole dish, arrange in layers the stuffing, beans, almonds and chicken.
Pour soup mixed with milk over mix.
Moisten 1 1/3 cups crumbs with 1/4 cup hot water and 2 tablespoons butter to spread on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes until bubbly hot.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In cold skillet, put ground beef, chopped onion and green pepper. Salt and pepper to taste. Stir with fork until browned. Pour in chili sauce, catsup and sugar. Stir until well combined. Cover and simmer gently for 20 to 30 minutes. Uncover and continue cooking until mixture is thick enough to spread.

title: apple cherry pie
directions: Pour fruit in pie dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon tapioca.
Put slits in top of dough.
Brush with milk.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 425° oven 40 minutes or until brown.
tags: Thank You brand apple pie filling

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and sprinkle with the remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Makes a large recipe.
May be cut in half.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook and stir occasionally (first 3 ingredients) until mixture turns silver. Add the peanuts. Cook until caramel colored.
Add coconut and soda.
Stir and pour onto buttered pan.
Cool.
Break into pieces. Eat and enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop onions and fry with margarine.
Put into bottom of baking dish.
Put broccoli into boiling water until separated; drain. Put in baking dish.
Add 2 cups of cooked rice.
Pour two cans of soup over rice.
Add cheese on top.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chicken dinner in a dish
directions: Place rice on bottom of 3-quart baking dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over chicken and rice.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add crabmeat, bread and mayonnaise.
Mix together.
Fry or broil until golden brown.

title: crab salad
directions: Combine all together.
Serve in pita halves or atop fresh, baked bread.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: In large saucepan, combine margarine, milk, sugar and cocoa. Heat to boiling, then boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto wax paper.
Remove when cool.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix.
Pour in vanilla wafer or graham cracker crust.
Top with green or red cherries and pecan halves.

title: meat loaf or meat balls
directions: Mix well and pour into loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Mixture can be used to make meat balls.

title: thanksgiving cranberry delight
directions: Combine pineapple juice and water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, lemon juice, peel and nutmeg. Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Add sour cream; stir until thoroughly combined.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 8-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate. Garnish with strawberries.

title: trucker's over the road stew
directions: Cooking Vegetables:
Place 2 to 3 cups of water in a large pot, add 2 to 3 beef bouillon cubes and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and add the carrots and celery; cook for 10 to 15 minutes, then add the potatoes and cook for an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tortilla cheese bake
directions: In a bowl, mix soup, water, cilantro, cumin and chilies together.
Line a baking pan with 1 layer of tortilla chips. Sprinkle onions, green peppers and olives over chips.
Then add cheeses next.
Pour 1/4 of the soup mixture over the chips.
Keep repeating steps until all ingredients are gone.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover for last 15 minutes of baking to let it crisp.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheeses.
Add all ingredients to hot melted cheeses except tomato.
You will need to stir often.
Add tomato and serve hot with chips.
This can be refrigerated for later use.
Then reheat and enjoy.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and celery in oil until onion has a clear look.
Mix all ingredients, then pour into baking dish and warm in oven until bubbly.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix and spread.
Decorate with sprinkles or nuts, etc.

title: venison roast
directions: Cook roast in water to cover with garlic & onions for 5 - 6 hrs. at 275°.
Drain water off and add beef broth and the mushroom gravy.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: mother's sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Line pan with pastry.
Then alternate potatoes with sugar, spice, lemon juice and butter.
Pour the wine over this.
Cover with pastry shell and bake at 350° until brown.
Serve while warm.

title: holiday pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes; cream with sugar.
Add pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add gradually to creamed mixture.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375° in jelly roll pan (17 1/4 x 11 1/2 x 1-inch).
It looks like a cookie sheet with 4 sides. Turn onto towel which has been heavily dusted with confectioners sugar.
Roll (with towel) while warm, beginning with 11 1/2-inch side.
(Roll will be 17 1/4-inches long.)
Unroll when cool. Spread with filling and re-roll.
Refrigerate.
Slice as needed.

title: fruit salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with juice from fruit cocktail.
Add fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *May substitute dried onion flakes, dried celery flakes and perhaps a little extra milk.

title: strawberry roll cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip whites until meringue consistency and set aside.
In separate bowl, beat yolks with sugar and warm water. Then blend in baking powder and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Place wax paper on cookie sheet with edges.
Grease thoroughly with oil. Spread batter onto paper evenly.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Before removing from oven, take a piece of waxed paper and sprinkle sugar over it.
Remove cake from oven and flip onto paper.
Take a cold, wet cloth and smooth over the wax paper (on top of cake).
Peel paper off slowly.
Roll up with second piece of paper and let it cool.

title: flank steak fix-up
directions: Rub steak with garlic; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cut meat crosswise into 4 to 6 pieces.
In large skillet, cook bacon. Drain bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.

title: fancy onions
directions: Drain onions and place in casserole.
Add soup, pimento and sour cream.
Mix well and heat at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add sherry just before serving.

title: pasta soup
directions: Sort beans; rinse well. Cook for 10 minutes. Drain, then add 8 to 10 cups water. Bring to boil, then turn on medium heat and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally. When half done, add all of the ingredients. Cook another hour until beans are done, stirring occasionally. (Cook to thickness desired.)

title: company oyster stew
directions: Strain oysters, saving liquid.
Add onion to oysters; heat in liquid until edges curl.
Into a heavy saucepan, put celery and milk; simmer about 3 minutes.
Add cream and butter; bring to the boiling point.
Turn off heat and slowly add oysters.
Add seasonings.
Keep hot, but never let boil from this point.
Serve in hot soup plates with crackers.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop the broccoli, cauliflower and green onions in a large salad bowl.
Add the bacon bits and mix well.
In a separate container, mix the mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over the vegetables.
Mix and store in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
This is better if you make a day ahead of time.
For a different taste, substitute lemon juice for the vinegar.
Also you can add chopped egg, fresh tomatoes and/or pimento for color and entirely different taste.

title: chocolate truffle
directions: Cream the butter in a large bowl.
Combine confectioners sugar and cocoa; add alternately with vanilla and heavy cream to butter. Blend well.
Chill until firm.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional confectioners sugar, cocoa or toasted chopped nuts of your choice.
Makes about 3 dozen candies.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain cherries and mandarin oranges.
Do not save this juice. Save the juice of the peaches, pears and pineapple and cook with the pudding mixes until thickens.
Cool completely and add fruit.

title: strawberry fluff icing
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, salt and 2/3 cup strawberries in top of double boiler.
Beat about 1 minute to blend.
Place over rapidly boiling water and beat constantly (with sturdy eggbeater or at high speed of an electric mixer) 7 minutes, or until frosting will stand up in stiff peaks.
Remove from boiling water; beat until cool, then fold in remaining drained berries and spread at once.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter.
Beat until fluffy and light.
Gradually add Cool Whip and powdered sugar; continue beating until smooth.
Spoon into crusts and place in icebox for several hours.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat egg whites. Mix rest of ingredients.
Fold in egg whites. Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: friendship stew
directions: Mix everything except beef in a large pot.
After browning beef, drain and add to pot.
Simmer for several hours.
Great on a cold day!!

title: pizza dough
directions: In glass mix yeast, sugar and water.
Mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes or until foamy.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, paprika and pepper.
Put milk in a bowl. Dip meat in milk, then in crumbs.
Place in foil lined pan.
Cover with foil; bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven; remove foil.
Pour on butter; bake for 15 minutes more at 425°, uncovered.

title: after dinner mints
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan. Boil, without stirring, to 265° (very firm ball stage). Pour on oiled slab or in shallow pan. Cool; lift (avoiding a stirring motion). Pull keeping the grain all one way. During pulling, sprinkle with a few drops of flavoring using vanilla, orange extract, lemon, oil of peppermint, wintergreen, clove or cinnamon. Add food coloring at same time if you like. When candy is too stiff to pull, stretch in longest rope possible (1/2 inch thick); cut in small pieces with scissors. Coat with powdered sugar. Store in covered glass jar and keep in warm place several days before serving.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together; drain.
Add all other ingredients and simmer together until hot, about an hour.
Do not drain beans, hominy or tomatoes.

title: muscadine jelly
directions: Crush fully ripe grapes.
Add
water
and simmer for 10 minutes.

in	jelly

Pour into glasses and cover with paraffin.
Add lids.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dinner rolls, well.
Separate dinner rolls.
You will have 4 rectangles as you do not separate the perforated lines.
Spoon mixture onto roll dough.
Seal 4 corners.
Brush top with melted oleo.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Take each biscuit and roll flat.
Cut in half.
Take each apple slice and wrap biscuit completely around it.
Makes 20 dumplings.
Grease Pyrex dish and place wrapped apples in dish close together.
Take 1 stick of margarine and dot over top of biscuits.
Mix sugars, cinnamon, vanilla and water together. Pour over top of dumplings.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: percolator punch
directions: Put juice, water and sugar in bottom of pot.
Spices in top. If you want to make just ordinary pot (10 cups), cut down 1/3 of everything.
Serves 30.

title: baked chicken
directions: Make cornbread from Mother's Best cornmeal mix.
Bake thick; be sure it is done.
Use buttermilk and 3 to 4 eggs.
Crumble cornbread in large bowl.
Add 3 to 4 slices loaf bread, minced onion and celery salt.
Add sage, one can cream of chicken soup and chicken broth; mash with potato masher.
Put in pan and fork it loosely with fork.
Barely bake in oven.
Fork loosely before serving.

title: canned peaches
directions: Peel peaches; cut in half and remove seed.
Fill each jar with peaches; add sugar.
Fill with water.
Add 2 quarts water to pressure canner.
Put cans in canner; bring pressure to 10 pounds and cut off.
Let pressure go all the way down before opening.

title: plum sauce
directions: Bring the water, lemon juice, sugar, cinnamon and cloves to a boil.
Add the plums; simmer, stirring constantly, until the skins are shriveled.
Remove the plums with a slotted spoon.
Reduce the remaining liquid by half; strain and pour over the fruit.
Allow to cool.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chili beans
directions: Wash beans through several changes of water.
Place in large pan.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Next day, heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook until beans are tender, about 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: nine day cabbage salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, blend well, toss with hands. Combine last 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour boiling hot dressing over cabbage and mix well.
Allow to cool.

title: white potato casserole
directions: Mix everything together except potatoes.
Partly thaw potatoes and stir in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt together. Let stand 3 hours. Mix sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and vinegar together. Bring to a boil. Drain cucumbers and onions and add to other mixture. Heat thoroughly; do not boil. Pour in jars.

title: saucy potatoes for company
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add flour, stirring until well blended.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in potatoes and pimiento.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crust.

title: green bean and red potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, garlic, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Wash but do not peel potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Drain and cool. Skins may be slipped off or left on.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices and toss in warm vinaigrette.
Steam beans briefly and toss with potatoes.
Sprinkle on dill or basil.
Serve slightly warm for best flavor.

title: easy dressing
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix all together and stuff in small hen or over doves in layers.
Cook for about 1 hour at 350°, depending on the size of your fowl.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Save 1/4 cup powdered sugar for dusting Reynolds Wrap.
Add remaining sugar, butter, extracts, and enough cream to make stiff dough.
Place dough on dusted Reynolds Wrap and knead slightly. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick and spread thinly with crunchy peanut butter.
Lift edge nearest you and roll up, as a jelly roll.
Cut roll with sharp knife and spread thinly with crunchy peanut butter. Lift edge nearest you and roll up, as a jelly roll.
Cut roll with sharp knife and pieces on waxed paper.
Let set for a few minutes before transferring to a large container.
Do not refrigerate but keep covered and dry.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread according to directions.
Crumble 1/2 in bottom of baking pan or dish.
Layer vegetables and bacon in order given, saving enough bacon for top.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and salad pickle.
Spread over vegetables and bacon layer.
Add remaining cornbread on top.
Chill until served.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in 5-quart casserole.
In 2 1/2-quart bowl, combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil on full power.
Takes approximately 3 minutes.
Boil mixture for 3 minutes, stirring several times.
Remove mixture from oven and stir in baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn.
Coat evenly. Put coated popcorn in microwave for 3 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
This coats popcorn more evenly.
As corn cools, it becomes crisp.
Store in airtight container.

title: cheese cake
directions: Stir cheese until soft.
Blend 1/2 cup milk into cream cheese. Add rest of milk and gradually add pudding.
Beat slowly, 1 minute.
Pour into crust.
Chill.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in butter until golden.
Remove from heat and add crumbs and two eggs.
Stir this mixture and cheese into chuck.
Add salt, pepper and crumbled bouillon.
Put half of meat mixture in greased loaf pan.
Arrange hard-boiled eggs in a row on top of meat.
Add remaining meat mixture; press firmly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Pour off drippings.

title: low-fat strawberry tiramisu
directions: In a large bowl, beat light cream cheese and powdered sugar until well blended. Gradually fold in whipped topping to blend. In a small bowl, combine coffee and liqueur, if desired.
Line an 8 x 8 inch glass baking dish with enough ladyfinger halves to cover bottom.
Place rounded sides down.
If necessary, cut lady fingers to fit dish.
Spoon 1/3 cup coffee mixture evenly over ladyfingers.
Top with 1/3 of cheese mixture (about 1 cup) spreading evenly.
Layer 1/3 of the strawberries (1 rounded cup) over cheese.
Repeat layers two more times ending with cheese. Place remaining strawberries on top.
Sift cocoa powder over top. Cover and refrigerate.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Saute sausage, onion and celery.
Boil squash and scoop out pulp.
Add to 1/2 cup stuffing mix and Parmesan cheese.
Stuff shells.
In greased casserole, put the tomato sauce and then add squash and bake at 350° for 35 minutes; after 25 minutes, add grated cheese on top of each squash.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine butter, sugar and cocoa.
Stir over low heat until just warm.
Add milk; bring to a boil and boil rapidly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Will keep in refrigerator for a long time.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of the pear juice.
Let set, then whip in softened cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and diced pears.
Let set.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion in large skillet. Drain.
Add rice, water and seasoned salt.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes on medium heat or until rice is done.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan or soup kettle, saute onion in butter. Add potatoes and water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in the milk, soup, garlic salt and pepper; heat through. Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted. Garnish with parsley. Yield: 10 servings (2 1/2 quarts).

title: chocolate fantasy pie
directions: Mix pecans, butter and flour.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Regular pie crust can be substituted, if desired.)

title: strike-it-rich cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven.
Poke holes at once down through the cake to the pan with round handle of a wooden spoon.
Holes should be at 1-inch intervals.
Only after poking holes, combine pudding mix with sugar in large bowl.
Gradually stir in milk. Then beat at low speed for not more than 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Quickly before pudding thickens, pour about 1/2 of the thin pudding evenly over warm cake and into the holes to make the strips.
Allow remaining pudding to thicken slightly; then spoon over the top, swirling it to frost the cake.
Chill at least one hour.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: braised pork medallions with apple
directions: Slice pork crosswise into eight medallions.
Mix seasoning together and coat pork.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Cook pork on both sides until brown.
Remove from pan and reserve.
Cover and keep warm.
Add onion and apple to skillet.
Cook until golden. Add apple cider to skillet; heat to a simmer.
Put pork slices in simmering liquid.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: onion casserole
directions: Layer onions, potatoes, cheese, onions, potatoes, cheese, soup and milk.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend ingredients.
Roll into bite size balls.
Cook 15 minutes at 375° or 400°.

title: amish fruit slush
directions: Mix sugar and water; boil for 5 minutes to make a syrup. Cool, then add pineapple, undiluted orange juice and bananas. Freeze.
Serve slightly thawed.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; wash and dry.
Rub margarine over each and roll in onion soup mix.
Wrap and seal in double thickness of foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg. Mix well. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Stir in chopped apples and vanilla. Pour into greased 8 x 8 pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: zucchini zebra brownies
directions: Beat first 10 ingredients in large bowl for 1 minute.
Beat remaining ingredients in separate bowl.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese batter over, then the rest of the batter.
Draw knife through pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut-oatmeal-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon onto cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes (estimate). Makes 8 dozen medium size cookies.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter together.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar.
Cream well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Spread in a well-greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: crab meat puffs
directions: Combine margarine and cheese spread until smooth and creamy. Add crab meat, both salts and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spread on English muffins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla butternut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar on High speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time; beating well.
Add 1 cup flour; beat at slower speed for 1 minute.
Add remaining flour and milk alternately, beating until well mixed.
Add flavoring.
Pour into three (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and spread in ungreased pan.
Mix rest of ingredients, except margarine.
Melt margarine and pour over mix. Stir and sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in heavy saucepan. Stir in gradually the hot water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute. Beat a little of the hot mixture into egg yolks, then beat into hot mixture in the saucepan. Boil 1 minute longer. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Stir until smooth. Blend in remaining ingredients. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and bake to a delicate brown at 350°.

title: rhode island clam (quahog) chowder
directions: *Flour and water, mixed, may be added to thicken chowder before adding butter.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and soda. Combine butter, sugars and pudding mix. Add eggs.
Gradually add flour. Stir in oats.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: praline cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine well.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to first mixture. Add pecans and mix well.
Drop in scant spoonfuls on greased baking sheets.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for about 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: cheese and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all ingredients together and mix with macaroni.
Put aside enough cheese for the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: italian meat sauce
directions: In large skillet, cook onion in hot oil until almost tender. Add meat and garlic; brown lightly.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer uncovered 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until sauce has thickened, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: dill dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together with a spoon.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: red velvet cake with marshmallow frosting
directions: Cream liquid Butter Buds, sugars and Egg Beaters.
Make a paste with 2 tablespoons liquid Butter Buds, cocoa and food coloring; add to creamed mixture.
Mix buttermilk with lite salt, soda and vanilla.
Add alternately with flour to cream mixture.
Beat 3 minutes after this is added.
Bake in two 9-inch pans that have been sprayed with nonfat cooking spray for 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack for a few minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Seven-Ups.
Chill.
Add Seven-Ups just before serving.
Serves 21.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Crumble sausage into medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown.
Stir occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of a buttered 9 x 3-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over sausage. Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes or until set; let stand 5 minutes and cut into squares.

title: chocolate fluffy frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Put bowl in a pan of cracked ice.
Beat ingredients with electric mixer until it forms peaks. This frosting does not harden.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and chill until you can roll in balls (3 hours).
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.

title: famous broccoli cheese soup
directions: Spray Dutch oven with Pam.
Add all veggies except potatoes and stir-fry until tender.
Add water, bouillon and potatoes. Cook until potatoes are crisp-tender.
Add cubed cheese; stir until melted.
Then mix skim milk and flour together and add to soup; stir until thick and creamy.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Bring to a boil in a large saucepan the first 4 ingredients. Add soda.
Bring to a boil again.
Then add pecans.
Stir constantly, continuing to firm ball stage.
Remove from heat; add teaspoon vanilla and beat until it thickens and loses shiny gloss. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Add few drops of hot water if it begins to get too hard.
Keep in airtight container.
Can freeze.

title: aunt ease's tomato relish
directions: Put sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed, salt and ground cloves in cooking pot.
Mix well, then add vinegar.
Bring to boil.
Add tomatoes, pepper and onions.
Cook 15 minutes, then can.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt in top of a double boiler, marshmallows and add milk. In a large bowl crumble vanilla wafers.
(Save inside wrapper and box to pack cake in.)
Pour marshmallow and milk mixture over vanilla wafer crumbs.
Add other ingredients, crushing and packing together.
Place ingredients inside the wrapper and tape to hold closed.
Place bag inside box and press firmly until bag conforms to shape of box.
Tape box to seal in flavor.
Place in refrigerator for 2 weeks before serving.

title: no salt deli dills
directions: Place cucumbers in ice water for 12 hours.
Drain.
If desired, slice into spears or chunks.
Into each clean, hot pint jar, place 1 garlic clove, 1 piece hot pepper, 1 slice horseradish, 1 grape leaf and 1 dill head.
Pack with cucumbers. Combine the vinegar and water in a pan; bring to boil.
Pour hot mixture over the cucumbers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal. Process in a boiling water bath canner for 10 minutes.
Cool undisturbed for 24 hours.
Let stand for 2 weeks before sampling. Makes 8 pints.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then beat together 2 minutes. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased only on the bottom.
Very good with cream cheese frosting.

title: pecan candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix 1 cup Pet milk and 2 cups sugar. Bring to a boil and boil for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Add 2 cups chopped pecans and 1/4 stick butter.
Stir 3 minutes more.
Then remove from fire and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until glossy.
Pour in a greased pan.

title: snow biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine rest of ingredients. Roll to 1-inch thickness.
Cut out and place in greased pan.
Let rise about 40 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 24.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Can also add crab or shrimp, if desired.
Serve over fettucine or angel pasta hair noodles.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: You may use food coloring.
You "must" mix on high for 10 minutes.
This is as good as any bakery frosting.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Melt the margarine in a large heavy saucepan, similar to a Dutch oven.
Add sugar and vinegar into the saucepan.
Add a small amount of water.
Add cabbage; simmer until very tender.
Stir in jelly just before serving.
If desired, more jelly can be added and also red food coloring.
This cabbage freezes very well.

title: pizza hut cavatini
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Drain.
Boil noodles according to directions on box.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in baking dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put back in oven and melt.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam or cook squash in a little water until done; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Bring to a boil the soup, gelatin, cream cheese and water. Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: fresh fruit compote
directions: Pour milk and orange juice into a bowl; add pudding.
Beat slowly with mixer for 1 minute; add whipped topping, beat 1 minute longer.
Put half of fruit in the bottom of a compote or serving dish.
Add pudding mixture.
Top with remaining fruit.
Chill.
Top with more whipped topping, if desired.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix thoroughly the sugar, eggs, oil, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add flour mixture; fold in cooked prunes and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Place batter into greased baking pan.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet, drain grease and add seasoning. Mix ingredients in large serving bowl.
Stir well and serve.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix, lemon pepper, dill weed, garlic powder and salad oil.
Pour over crackers.
Stir in bowl or shake in bag until coated.
Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bonnie's chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix together and cook over a double boiler. Pour into baked pie crust.

title: soup beans
directions: Cover beans plus 1 tablespoon salt to soak overnight.
Add ham bone, beans and water in kettle. Cook until tender. Add bacon grease or Crisco to make soup thick.
Serve with cornbread and fried potatoes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip all ingredients together until smooth.
Put into pie shell and refrigerate.
Top with whipped topping.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish, layer onion and potatoes.
Add milk, dot with butter and add salt and pepper.
Add corned beef hash; follow with corn.
Top with crumbs and cover and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Uncover and bake 25 minutes.

title: yum yum chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove skin.
Bone.
Cut chicken in small pieces.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together the soup and sour cream.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle corn bread stuffing mix on top.
Melt 1 cup margarine with 1 cup chicken broth.
Pour over casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine pork and beans, brown sugar, mustard and catsup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with diced bacon.
Bake at 325° for 2 or 2 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In bowl, dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cranberry sauce. Spoon into 8-inch square pan.
Spoon sour cream on top and stir through to marble.

title: orange chicken and rice skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook and stir 3 minutes. Drain. Reduce heat to medium. Stir in combined mayonnaise, juice and sugar. Add rice and green pepper. Bring to boil. Remove from heat. Add oranges and pineapple. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.

title: wild rice-mushroom soup
directions: Bring 1 can chicken broth to a boil in a small saucepan; remove from heat.
Add mushrooms; let stand 30 minutes.
Drain well, reserving mushroom liquid.
Coarsely chop mushrooms; set aside.

title: okra pickles
directions: Wash and dry okra.
Pack in quart jars with hot peppers and dill.
Mix vinegar, water, salt and pickling spice.
Have okra in hot bath while vinegar mixture comes to a boil.
Pour over okra and seal.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix together with electric mixer until creamy.
Spread in bottom of dish.
Top with layer of lettuce, onions, tomatoes, cheese and olives.

title: grilled chicken breasts
directions: Whisk lemon juice, oil, garlic and rosemary together.
Pour over chicken breasts arranged in a shallow dish.
Salt and pepper. Marinate at least 4 hours, turning a few times.
Grill over hot coals 4 to 6 minutes per side, brushing with marinade.

title: chicken-string bean casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and cut into small pieces. Cook rice in the chicken broth until tender.
Mix chicken, soup, rice and beans.
Pour into a large casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hobo can cake
directions: Mix soda, raisins, rum and boiling water.
Cover and let set for 2 hours.
Mix all other ingredients.
Add to raisins, water and soda.
Divide batter into greased (three 1-pound) coffee cans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from cans to wire rack to cool.
Place on side to slice.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine diced chicken with grapes, celery, pecans and onions. Stir salad dressing and mustard together and toss with chicken mixture. Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Keep in covered bottle or jar.
Shake well before using.
Store in refrigerator.

title: san francisco chicken salad
directions: You will need a baking bag.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio, jello and crushed pineapple. Add sour cream, marshmallows, Cool Whip and nuts. Mix all together. Chill and serve.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Partially bake pie crusts at 400° for 6 minutes on preheated cookie sheet. Reduce heat to 350°. In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook chopped green onions and green peppers with garlic until tender. In medium bowl, beat at high speed the milk, soup, eggs and flour until well mixed. Stir in onions and pimentos. Distribute broccoli and cheese evenly between 2 baked crusts. Carefully pour filling over broccoli and cheese. Bake pies on cookie sheet 50 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 to 15 minutes on wire rack. Makes 2 pies or 12 servings.

title: one dollar salad(ha!)
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and mix with jello and boil 5 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, celery, nuts and pimentos and add to jello mixture.
Add prepared Dream Whip.

title: ice box fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers into powder.
Add fruit and nuts.
Wet with milk and mold into tube pan. If dry add a little cherry juice into batter.
Put into grease tube pan with butter.
Put into ice box for a few days before cutting.
Decorate with pineapple slices, nuts and cherries.

title: quick homemade biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with spoon.
It should be very stiff.
Put 2 tablespoons of oil in skillet and oil hands well.
Put a big spoonful of dough in hands and roll into a ball. Place in oiled skillet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yield:
8 biscuits.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, carrots, celery and water for 20 minutes. Drain and save water.
Saute butter and onions until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, potatoes, carrots and celery.
Add water (saved) one cup at a time until desired thickness.

title: cranberry crumb bars
directions: Mix 2 cups flour with oats, sugar and margarine until crumbly. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of oats mixture.
Press remaining in bottom of greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In small bowl, mix cranberry sauce with marmalade, almonds and remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Spoon over oat mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining oat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into squares to serve.

title: watermelon (spiced) pickles
directions: Use firm rind of watermelon.
Trim off green skin and pink flesh and cut into 1-inch cubes.
Soak overnight in the salt and 1 quart water mixed together.
Drain.
Cover with fresh water; cook until tender.
Drain.
Boil together the remaining 2 quarts water, sugar, vinegar and spices (may also tie in a piece of cheesecloth) for 5 minutes.
Add the rind and cook until transparent, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove spices.
Pack in hot sterile jars and seal immediately if storing for long periods.

title: maple nut biscuit ring
directions: Lightly grease Bundt pan.
Melt butter; stir in nuts, brown sugar and syrup.
Pour 1/4 cup of this into Bundt pan.
Tear each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Put into pan; pour remaining sugar mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool 3 minutes and invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.

title: lasagna(microwave)
directions: Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes. Stir once. Stir in tomato sauce and water. Cover with lid and cook on High 4 to 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and parsley.
Mix well.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of meat and sauce mix in 12 x 8-inch casserole.
Place 4 uncooked noodles over sauce. Top with 1/2 cheese mixture.
Put 1/4 of the Mozzarella cheese next.
Repeat. End with meat mixture. Cover tightly with plastic wrap. Cook on High for 15 minutes.
Rotate dish and cook on Medium power (50%) for 15 minutes.
Remove wrap. Cook on High 2 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes.

title: blueberry nut crunch cake
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread undrained pineapple over the bottom of pan.
Add layer of blueberries and 3/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit and sugar, then pour melted margarine all over the layer of dry cake mix.
Top with chopped pecans.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
After baking 25 minutes, use a knife to cut down to the bottom of cake in several places.
This will let the juice come up.

title: pepperoni calzones
directions: Punch down dough.
Divide into 6 equal parts.
Roll each part into 7-inch circle on lightly floured surface.
Mix tomato sauce, mushrooms, basil, oregano and garlic. Spread over half of each circle to within 1-inch of edge. Top with pepperoni, bell pepper and cheese. Fold dough carefully over filling.
Pinch edges to seal securely.
Place sandwiches on greased cookie sheet.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Brush sandwiches with egg. Bake about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potatoes and bananas
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in pot, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Peel bananas and cut into chunks.
Toss with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Place potatoes and bananas in a shallow roasting pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Drizzle with rum and melted butter. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and mash or puree potatoes, bananas and all of the liquid.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish; cover with aluminum foil and warm in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: smoked eel stew of the northeast tribes
directions: Simmer all together in a large heavy kettle for about 1 hour or until the potatoes are tender.
Skim off excess fat.
Serve hot.

title: butterhorn cookies
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Mix egg yolk and sour cream.
Add to flour and mix thoroughly.
Divide dough into 3 portions and chill several hours or overnight. `Roll each portion into a 12-inch circle.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle mixture on dough.
Cut each circle into 16 wedges.
Roll each wedge firmly, starting at outside edge.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes until lightly browned.

title: beef-eggplant skillet
directions: Brown beef and onion in a small amount of hot fat.
Sprinkle flour over meat; stir.
Add tomato sauce, water, ground pepper, oregano, chili powder and salt.
Mix well.
Season eggplant with salt and pepper.
Arrange slices over meat.
Cover.
Simmer, until eggplant is tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese.
Pass Parmesan.
Serves 4.

title: marinated slaw #2
directions: Mix together cabbage, pepper, onion and salt.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over this mixture and leave for 1 hour.
Drain, then add sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard seed and celery seed.
Mix well. Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: office punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl.
Add cherries and orange slices.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Place chops in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add onions, peppers, and tomatoes.
Combine ketchup, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, and bouillon; pour over vegetables.
Cover and bake at 350°F for about 1 1/2 hrs. or until chops are done and vegetables are tender.
Mix cornstarch and water until smooth; stir into liquid in dish.
Heat until thickened.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime for 12 hours or overnight.
Wash cucumbers 3 times in clean water and soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a low boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumber and soak for 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Boil pickles for 35 minutes. Fill in jars and pour syrup over cucumbers in jars.
Leave 1/8-inch headspace.
Process jars 5 minutes in boiling water. Start time when water gets to a full rolling boil.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well several hours before serving. Chill. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: pork chops and peach sauce
directions: Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add chops; brown on each side until done.
Transfer to a platter and keep warm.
Add water to skillet, scraping to loosen browned particles.
Add preserves and onion soup mix. Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add peaches; cook 1 minute.
Spoon over pork chops.

title: cheese and onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter; press into 9-inch pie plate.
Add onion rings, sauteed in butter until limp, and cover with grated cheese.

title: taffy - pull taffy
