directions: Combine all ingredients, except flavoring, in a saucepan. Cook without stirring to 268° to 270° or between the very hard ball and light crack stage.
Add choice of flavoring.
Pour candy into a large buttered platter.
Cool until finger imprints can be seen or until candy can be handled.
Butter hands; pull taffy. Repeat until taffy has a satin-like sheen.
Form into shapes, roll or braids.
Cut into bite-size pieces.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding.
Add other ingredients.
Stir well and chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together, adding chips just before serving.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown ground meat and onions.
Drain.
Add rice, beans and nacho cheese until heated.
Put in pan; add cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Heat on 300° until cheese bubbles.

title: hamburg potato casserole
directions: Grease casserole generously.
Layer in casserole:
hamburg, potatoes, carrots and onions; salt and pepper each layer.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring peanut butter, water and oleo to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix well and add eggs and buttermilk.
Pour batter into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use Peanut Butter Frosting recipe while still warm.

title: texas hash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown meat and cook onions and pepper until tender.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Stir in peanut butter and dry ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet and press down with fork.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: marcia abrams' chicken
directions: Saute the onion in olive oil, adding one or two crushed garlic cloves when the onions are almost brown.
Add sliced mushrooms.
Let it all brown for a minute or two.
Then add chicken and brown on both sides.
Add white wine and tomatoes. Add seasonings to taste.
While it is simmering, add artichoke hearts.
Spread them out around bottom of pan so they will cook/thaw evenly.
Stir in a tablespoon each of mustard and capers.
Turn flame to low and simmer 10 to 20 minutes, or until chicken is done but not tough.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Empty pineapple into large mixing bowl.
Add coconut, marshmallows, cherries, juice and nuts.
Fold in whipping cream; whip cream and sugar together.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve over sliced angel food cake, pound cake or in parfait dish.
Top with whole cherry.

title: guacamole dip
directions: To get Lipton California Dip:
in a small bowl blend 1 envelope Lipton Onion Soup Mix with 2 c. (16 oz.)
Sour Cream.
Chill. Blend the cup of mixture above with the remaining ingredients listed and chill.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Put cottage cheese in blender until creamy. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour a spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and leave cake in oven for 2 more hours.
Top with cherries or blueberries! Enjoy!

title: endless slaw
directions: Bring last seven ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, onion and peppers.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 or 60 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: picante turkey pasta
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey with onion and green pepper until turkey loses its pink color,
stirring frequently and breaking up turkey into small pieces.
Add tomatoes, corn, spices and picante sauce; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes,
stirring occasionally.
While turkey simmers, cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Stir pasta into turkey mixture; let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Melt margarine and combine with flour and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix milk with pudding and spread over cream cheese layer.
Add remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Lasts in refrigerator several days.

title: chili verde
directions: Flour meat and brown in fat.
Add onion and garlic and cook. Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Great in burritos, over rice, etc.
Very mild.

title: catfish gumbo
directions: Cut fillets into 1-inch pieces.
Cook celery, green pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add broth, tomatoes, okra and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add fish.

title: egg chili dish
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
For thick dish put in 7 1/2 x 11-inch or thinner 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: With mixer, beat margarine, Crisco, sugar and eggs. In a separate bowl, sift all dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture alternately with milk. Mix well. Add vanilla. Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Cool slightly in pan, then turn out onto plate.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, stir together all ingredients except apples.
Fold in apples.
Put into a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan, including beets.
Cook for 3 minutes until mixture thickens.
Let cool, then sore in refrigerator.

title: celery seed bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine butter, celery seed and parsley flakes, stirring well to blend.
Spread on cut slices of each roll.
Place on baking sheet and broil until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine zucchini, eggs and parsley. In a small bowl, combine baking mix, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt and add to zucchini mixture.
Stir just enough to dampen dry ingredients.
Heat olive oil and butter in a large skillet.
Drop batter from a spoon into the heated oil and brown pancakes lightly on both sides.
Keep warm in a 300° oven until all are cooked.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Mix with onion and pepper.

title: lemon or chocolate lush
directions: Mix and pat down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix oatmeal and pecans together in large bowl.
Set aside. In medium saucepan, mix cocoa and sugar until well blended.
Add other ingredients and bring to rolling boil.
Pour over oatmeal and pecans, combining thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper. Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook the carrots that have been scraped and sliced crosswise until just barely done, not too soft.
Drain thoroughly.
Marinate in mixture of the remaining ingredients, except onion and green pepper, which have been whipped together in blender until smooth. Put in bowl.
Add the sliced onion and green pepper.
Marinate overnight.
Store in airtight container.
Keeps a long time stored in refrigerator.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Have ready wire rack(s) on a cookie sheet and lightly greased shallow, oval baking dish.
Put egg white and water into a shallow dish and beat with a fork until egg is well broken up.
Spread bread crumbs on waxed paper.
Dip eggplant in egg mixture, then bread crumbs to coat.
Put slices on rack. Spray lightly with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake about 30 minutes until tops are golden brown.
Turn slices over and spray again. Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until tops are golden brown and crisp and centers are soft.

title: clubhouse chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken on both sides in oil.
Stir in the tomatoes, mushrooms, green peppers, onion, water, italian seasoning, and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat - cover and simmer for 10-15 minutes or until juices from chicken run clear.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in shortening, then add onion and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook about 1/2 of 14 ounce bag of sea shell macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse, then add to meat mixture.
Add 1 cup cream of mushroom soup.
Pour in baking dish.
Top mixture with 1 cup grated cheese and bake about 30 minutes or until cheese is completely melted, at 350°.

title: corn relish
directions: Drain corn, reserving 1/4 cup of liquid in saucepan; combine all remaining ingredients and heat to a boil.
Simmer for 15 minutes; then let cool.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad with pecans
directions: Mix salad dressings.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: sausage quesadillas
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain well.
Set aside.
Arrange 4 tortillas on cookie sheet.
Divide sausage and cheeses evenly over 4 tortillas.
Sprinkle on jalapeno pepper.
Place remaining 4 tortillas on top of sausage mixture.
Brush tops with oil.
Bake at 400°
for 7 to 10 minutes.
Cut in wedges.

title: chinese beef
directions: Cook beef until brown and crumbly.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Arrange peas on top; cover with celery.
Mix together soup, milk, salt, pepper and onions.
Pour over casserole mixture. Sprinkle chips on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel and mash avocado.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in airtight container; store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Make pudding using 3 cups milk.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Place one layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Spread half of the pudding mix on top.
Add another layer of graham crackers, then the rest of the pudding mix, and finally a top layer of graham crackers.
Top with icing and refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: layered parfait mold
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add mixed fruit; stir until fruit is separated and gelatin is thickened.
Chill, if necessary.
Pour into 6 cup ring mold. Chill until set, but not firm.
Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Blend in softened ice cream; chill until slightly thickened.
Spoon over layer in mold.
Chill until firm, 4 hours.
Unmold on serving plate.
Makes about 6 cups or 10 to 12 servings.

title: creamy fruit spread
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients. Chill for 3 hours or longer.
Form into ball.
Garnish with nuts and orange rind.
Serve with apple or pear slices, gingersnaps or vanilla wafers.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump pineapple, fruit cocktail and oranges, undrained, in bowl and then add pudding mix and coconut.
Refrigerate.
Add bananas just before serving or omit if planning to keep for several days.

title: sherbet punch
directions: In large punch bowl, mix all ingredients.
Pour into punch cups.
Enjoy!

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Season inside of chicken with salt and pepper.
Place quartered onion in cavity.
Place chicken, breast side up, on rack in roasting pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: deer chili "camp style"
directions: Brown venison and beef in a large covered pan.
Add chopped onion and 2 tablespoons chili powder and cook for 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce and cook over low heat for 15 minutes, then add chili beans and simmer (stirring occasionally) for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over toasted onion rolls.
Yields about 4 quarts.

title: low-fat turkey chili
directions: Note:
Seasoning amounts depend on personal preference.
Taste during cooking and add additional chili powder, pepper and garlic as needed.

title: carrot and zucchini bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder, ginger and baking soda.
In another large bowl, stir together eggs, carrots, zucchini, raisins, walnuts, oil, honey and vanilla.
Add carrot mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Place a piece of chicken in a piece of dried beef and roll up. Wrap the bacon around the chicken and place in a glass dish or long pan.
Combine the sour cream and soup and pour over the chicken. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and serve or set aside.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Enjoy!

title: boiled bacon dressing
directions: Fry bacon slowly.
In
a
saucepan, put sugar with salt and cornstarch.
Mix thoroughly.
Add
beaten egg and vinegar. Cook to desired thickness.	This
is
a
hot dressing for over dandelion, endive or garden lettuce.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in oleo, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press spaghetti mixture into a buttered 10-inch pie plate, forming a crust.
In a large skillet, brown beef.
Drain well.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar and oregano.
Heat through.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti crust.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350'° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top.
Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: ham delights
directions: Mix ham, cheese, margarine, mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce together well.
Split rolls and spread mixture on bottom half.
Top with other half.
Cover with foil. Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Can be frozen and heated when needed. Cook 20 to 30 minutes, if frozen.
Makes 60 servings.

title: holiday cordial
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in liqueur. Refrigerate in airtight container.
Stays fresh one month.

title: creamy cabbage slaw
directions: In serving dish, combine shredded cabbage and sliced onion. In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt; stir until sugar is dissolved and ingredients are well blended.
Drizzle mayonnaise mixture over cabbage mixture in bowl. Toss lightly to mix well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a shallow 3-quart baking dish with cooking spray.

title: toad in the hole
directions: Make batter by sifting 4 ounces flour and pinch of salt; add 1 egg and about 1/3 of a half pint of milk.
Stir until smooth with wooden spoon, then stir in rest of milk.
Put 1 ounce shortening into baking pan.
Heat about 4 minutes; add sausage and heat 8 to 10 minutes.
Pour batter over sausages after they have heated through.
Cook in hot (450° to 475°) oven about 10 minutes, until beginning to rise.
Lower heat to moderate 375° oven and bake until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together, then mix all others and pour over chicken mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kona chicken
directions: Simmer sauce ingredients for 10 minutes.
Lay chicken pieces skin side down in sauce. Cover and simmer 25 minutes on each side. May be served hot or cold.

title: italian orange cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a very large bowl or pan. Make a deep well and put in the softened butter or margarine, orange rind, juice and eggs.
Work all this together until the dough holds well enough to roll.
Take a little dough at a time. Roll out on board and slice 1-inch widths and place not too close together on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: eclair party cake
directions: Mix 2 packages of instant French vanilla pudding with 3 cups of milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add one (8 ounce) Cool Whip.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with oleo and line with graham crackers, separated. Add layer of pudding, layer of graham crackers, layer of pudding, layer of graham crackers (top layer).

title: friendship cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Friendship Cake Starter, oil and eggs in bowl; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in electric skillet.
Cook at 280°, bringing to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Take off heat.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring to blend well.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool and dice.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: mini chocolate chip cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Paper-line or spray with cooking spray
30 muffin cups*.
Stir together crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter; press equal portions on bottom of prepared cups.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt 1 cup chips.
In larger mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon batter into cups.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake 20 minutes or until set; cool.
Refrigerate.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: fontenot fish
directions: Place catfish in large pot.
Add red pepper, salt, flour, tomato sauce, shortening, cloves of garlic and water.
Cook 30 minutes.
Do not stir more than necessary.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Fit 1 pie crust into bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Combine all other ingredients and spoon into the pie crust.
Fit the other pie crust on top of this mixture.
Mold and flute edges.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
(May spill over in oven.)

title: chocolate delight cake
directions: Combine
ingredients
and press into 1 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: In medium saucepan, melt morsels and margarine. Stir in crumbs and nuts until crumbly.
Press half the mixture firmly into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: mother's snickerdoodles
directions: Cream the butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until light.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs in, one at a time.
Add sifted flour with soda and cream of tartar.
Mix well; roll into small balls.
Drop balls into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400°.
These flatten out and crinkle.

title: easy appetizers
directions: Brown sirloin and sausage in frying pan; drain.
Cube cheese and add to meat.
Add spices and heat until cheese completely melts.
Spread meat and cheese mixture on party rye slices.
Place under broiler for 5 minutes or until browned on top.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover, cook over low heat for 45 minutes. Stir now and then uncover.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate muffins
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Sift the next 5 ingredients.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Fill cupcake paper 1/3 full (batter is very runny).
Add 1 well rounded teaspoonful of cheese mixture in middle.
Top with chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 24 to 30 cupcakes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and press in a 9 x	9
x
2-inch pan.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine and beat until thick.
Pour over cream cheese mixture. Top with 8 ounces Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in a greased deep dish pie plate or shallow round casserole.
Place in oven at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend well. Add oats, flour and nuts.
Mix these all together and drop by scant teaspoon about 2-inches apart on a foiled lined cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Watch closely. Let cool on foil and they will flip off making bottoms smooth.
Mix by hand instead of electric mixer.
Double this receipt to make 8 dozen.

title: 4 layer pie
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, oleo and pecans, then spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ghost cookies
directions: Melt white chocolate bark in double boiler. Dip cookies into melted chocolate and cool on wire racks. When cooled, but not set, add 2 chocolate chips for the eyes. Let set.

title: new york strip steak florentine with sauteed mushrooms
directions: Heat butter and olive oil in large frying pan over medium to high heat.
When hot, add mushrooms and 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring or tossing occasionally.
Add chives, parsley, garlic and shallot, stirring them to blend in for 7 or 8 minutes.
Add cognac and lemon juice. Allow to simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Taste for seasoning.
Broil steaks to your preference (rare is best) and pour mushrooms over steaks.

title: art's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook in oven at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Use for pork chops, chicken, steak, hot dogs or hamburgers.

title: sausage and cheese grit casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 3-quart baking dish.
Bring water and salt to boil.
Slowly add grits.
Cover; cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and butter until melted.
Add eggs, milk and sausage; pour into dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: marilyn lonsdale's famous beans
directions: Brown beef; drain grease.
Put meat in a crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion; drain fat and add to crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients to crock-pot; stir together well.
Cover and cook on low setting for 4 to 9 hours.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Increase the heat and boil steadily, without stirring, until thermometer reaches 265° or until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all items together. Chill.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Cake: Use your favorite cake recipe or Duncan Hines "Butter Recipe Golden" cake mix. Make 3 layers whichever you use. Bake cake about 20 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: In large skillet cook ground beef, peppers and onion until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soup, sliced olives, salsa and water.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile, prepare corn muffin mix, following package directions.
Spread half of muffin batter into greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon the hot meat mixture over the muffin layer.
Carefully spread the remaining corn muffin batter over the meat mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30-35 minutes or until muffin layer is golden.
Top with cheese.
If desired, garnish with tomatoes and whole olives.
Cut into squares.
Serves 5-6.

title: pizzelles
directions: In blender, beat eggs until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar to beaten eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add melted margarine, vanilla, anise flavor and Sambuca.
Mix until well blended. Sift flour and baking powder together in a large bowl.
Add egg mixture and beat with hand mixer until smooth.
Batter will be sticky.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in center of pattern on pizzelle iron.
Heat until golden.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar through sifter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Add cream cheese and sour cream slowly to hot, mashed potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put in baking dish and brush top with melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie bars
directions: Bake crescent rolls on cookie or pizza sheet rolled out as crust at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread on cooled crust.
Press veggies into mixture, then top with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate 4 hours or more.
Great the next day!

title: chunky cranberry sauce
directions: Core apple and chop coarsely.
Toss in small bowl with lemon juice, draining off any extra juice.
Toss together apples, pears, celery and pecans.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Just before serving, drain any juice from fruit.
Stir cranberry sauce into fruit, breaking it into pieces.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 (4 cups).

title: lime honey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a tall jar.
Shake well. Refrigerate.
Lasts up to 10 days in refrigerator.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Add all dry ingredients first, then add all wet ingredients to the dry and mix well.
(Mix by hand or electric mixer.)
When blended, pour into a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss and chill for 3 hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, add 1 cup cherry tomato halves and 1 avocado, peeled and cubed.

title: tuna sandwiches
directions: Put tuna in strainer and pour boiling water over all.
Let drain good.
Mix all together; add mayonnaise to moisten.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry spinach salad
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Toss first 4 ingredients together. Spread almonds in single layer and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter and shortening, then add sugar, egg, flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Add vanilla.
Roll into 1-inch balls; flatten with glass bottom dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix together the oleo, sugar, egg, vanilla and salt.
Add the flour and stir in the mini chips.
Bake 16 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares while warm.

title: creamy pasta salad
directions: Combine spaghetti, broccoli and soup in casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sister mabel's caramel corn
directions: In 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring, over medium-high heat.
Boil to hard ball stage (260°).
Remove from heat; stir in soda and pour at once over popcorn in a large roasting pan.
Stir to coat.
Bake in a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: three in one casserole
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Add soup (no water) and green beans. Heat; spread in casserole dish.
Top with potatoes and cheese. Heat at 350° until cheese melts.

title: strawberry whip
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in boiling water. Add lemon juice, salt and sugar.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in berries and egg whites. Chill until firm.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Bake approximately 1 hour in greased and floured loaf pans at 350°.
Cool in pans.

title: baked scallops hearthside
directions: Place scallops sliced in half in pan.
Salt and pepper and pour wine and half of the butter over.
Cover with bread crumbs and pour remaining butter over.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Yields 2 servings.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Mix together butter and sugar in a saucepan.
Boil for one minute.
Let cool.
Add 1/4 cup sweet milk.
Sift into this confectioners sugar; beat until cold.
Add vanilla and frost cake.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Mix 1/2 cup Cheddar and all the Jack cheese with the chilies and put in the bottom of baked pie shell. Microwave the half and half, salt and cumin 2 minutes to heat. Do not let boil. Slightly beat the eggs and slowly add the hot milk mixture to the eggs. Pour over the cheese in the pie shell. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Microwave 8 to 9 minutes or until almost completely set. Let stand 8 to 10 minutes. Serve.

title: meringue
directions: Whip egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and whip until stiff, but not dry, until they stand in peaks and then lean over slightly when beater is removed.
Beat in sugar 1 tablespoon at a time.
Do not overbeat.
Beat in vanilla at end.

title: marshmallow coconut drops
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter in a large saucepan. Place over medium heat and cook to soft ball stage (230° to 234°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and marshmallow cream. Stir until marshmallow cream is melted.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool completely.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion and green chilies in butter.
Melt Velveeta and mix with onion and green chilies.
Add half and half and season with garlic salt.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: congo bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with butter or vegetable oil. Blend the flour, baking soda and salt in a small bowl with a wooden spoon. Set aside. Using an electric mixer on medium speed, cream the butter, sugar and vanilla in a medium-size bowl until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Stop the mixer once or twice to scrape the bowl with a rubber spatula. Add the eggs and mix on high speed for 3 seconds, then on medium speed until blended, about 5 seconds. Add the flour mixture and mix on low speed until almost blended, 8 to 10 seconds. Stop the mixer once to scrape the bowl. Add the chocolate chips and nuts and mix on low speed for 5 seconds. Finish the mixing by hand with a wooden spoon. Spread the batter evenly in the prepared pan. Bake the bars on center oven rack until the top has formed a rich, golden crust and dropped below the level of the darker golden outer edges, 30 minutes. These bars cannot be tested by inserting a tester because the inside remains gooey. Cool 30 minutes in the pan, placed on a rack before cutting.

title: chicken divan
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add flour, mixing until smooth. Gradually add the stock, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Add sherry, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Fold in the whipped cream.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange sweet potatoes in cook-and- serve baking dish.
In 1-quart saucepan, over medium heat, combine brown sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, simmer, stirring constantly, 5 minutes.
Pour syrup over sweet potatoes.
Bake 20 minutes or until sweet potatoes are well glazed, basting often with syrup.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Saute beef with onion until beef is done; drain.
Drain corn and peas.
Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Mix beef and onion mixture with corn, peas and undrained tomatoes.
Add noodles and place in large casserole dish.
Place enough grated Cheddar cheese to cover top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cheese should be bubbly.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Put rice and carrots in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix water and soups and pour half of mixture over rice.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle on mushrooms and top with rest of soup mixture. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
When serving, use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.
The pudding makes this rich and very good.

title: gone-all-afternoon-stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Put all in large casserole with lid to fit.
No need to brown meat first.
Mix ingredients together. Cover tightly and bake for 5 hours.
Serves 6.
Delicious!

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix together Crisco and sugar, then add egg and molasses.
Sift together and stir in other ingredients.

title: cool cucumber dip with fresh vegetables
directions: Cover with hot brine.
Apply caps and seal at once.
Invert until cool.

title: german style pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Fry or bake until done.
Place in casserole dish and add celery flakes and parsley flakes.
Mix envelope of Hunter sauce with 2 cups of water.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Pour over meat and simmer about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 3 to 6.

title: new orleans jambalaya
directions: Place 3 tablespoons oil in saucepan.
Add chopped onion, chopped green peppers, minced cloves of garlic, sliced celery and green onions.
Saute until limp.
Add tomatoes and chicken broth (covered); cook 1/2 hour or so.
Then add sausage (I use Hillshire Farms beef kielbasa), diced ham, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and thyme.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes.
Add raw rice. Cook 25 minutes more (covered).
Good hot or cold.

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Dip and coat chicken in flour and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown chicken in oil in hot skillet.
Place in Dutch oven or roaster.
Add a little water with chicken bouillon and sprinkle with onion powder.
Brown 2 tablespoons in skillet.
Add water. Thicken and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until done.

title: hot sauce and wieners
directions: Melt butter and brown onions; add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Let age in refrigerator for at least 1 day.
Boil wieners, cut and put in sauce.

title: beef stew
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour and slowly brown in oil in heavy pan. Brown and keep scratching all the "crunchy" from bottom of pan. Add water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until tender.
Add onion, potatoes and carrot.
More water may be added if needed. Thicken gravy with cornstarch and water if desired.

title: beautiful biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Cut Crisco into flour with fork.
Add milk and stir just enough to hold dough together.
Knead about 10 times.
Roll out dough 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits.
Place an inch apart on ungreased sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.
Makes 16 to 20.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix
well
and	chill,	then
roll into small balls and chill again.
Melt
bag
of	chocolate chips and a small piece
of paraffin
wax less than 1/4 bar.
Dip balls in this and place on waxed paper.

title: blue ribbon recipe(serves all)
directions: Good to the last drop.
Serve often.

title: peanut butter fun dough
directions: Beat all ingredients with electric mixer until smooth.
Mold and shape mixture as desired (example: ball, logs or squares). Eat it.

title: ma sowash's sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar; beat eggs.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients.
Next, chill and form balls.
Roll in sugar.
Sprinkle lightly with a few drops of water.
Bake until lightly browned, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift dry
ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients in order:
oil, eggs,
pumpkin and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan
at
375° for 1 hour.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken and ziti casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, stir together spaghetti sauce, ziti, chicken and 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Cut up chicken. Combine chicken, soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms, frozen vegetables, cheese and onions. Pour into a roasting pan and bake, covered, at 360° for 1 hour. Remove cover and stir. Sprinkle with almonds or croutons and bake 15 to 30 minutes more.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Mix together and fold in 2 beaten egg whites with a pinch of salt.
Pour into ovenproof pan, set in shallow pan of water.
Cook 30 minutes in slow (325°) oven.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture in 2 1/2-quart round glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding mixture. Chill thoroughly.
May garnish top with either halved strawberries or maraschino cherries (optional).

title: edith's jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water, then add 2 cups of cold water.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into Jell-O mold, can or pan, etc.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pennsylvania red cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a large pan. Add remaining ingredients. Cover tightly. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally. For crisp cabbage, cook 15 minutes. For old fashioned, cook 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with flour and blend.
Good hot or cold.

title: dirt cups(pudding)
directions: In mixing bowl, mix pudding according to box.
Add Cool Whip. Set aside.
Put 1/2 of the crushed cookies in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour pudding mix on top.
Top with remaining cookies.
Arrange gummy worms so they look like they're crawling in a dirt bed.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all together and put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream with mixer until creamy. Cut apples into slices. Dip apples in mixture. Store unused mixture in fridge.

title: special shortbread fingers
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla until soft and creamy.
Sift the flour; add gradually to butter mixture.
Blend well.
Chill for 2 hours.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll between palms of hands to shape like fingers.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until light golden color.
Transfer to cake rack to cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together until well mixed.
Add butter and oleo; mix well.
Beat eggs.
Add enough milk to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Pour into flour mixture.
Mix well.
Knead, adding flour until you reach right consistency.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mom's homemade pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Have butter and Crisco at room temperature.
Add sugar and cream together with butter and Crisco. Add eggs and cream.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add both mixtures together.
Add milk.
Cream until well mixed.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade butterfinger ice cream(for 4 quart churn)
directions: Mix chocolate milk, condensed milk and Cool Whip into a large mixing bowl.
Crush chilled Butterfinger candy bars with a rolling pin and add to mixture.
Pour into ice cream container.
White whole milk can be added to bring up to the "full" line.
Follow manufacturers directions to churn the ice cream.

title: pasta perfecto
directions: Toss pasta with tomato and other ingredients. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: green slime(great halloween punch)
directions: Prepare limeade per directions on can.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: granny clampett's possum stew
directions: Stir in a big pot over a fire.
Serves 8 (unless Jethro eats).

title: fresh strawberry pie recipe
directions: Cook ingredients and put aside to cool.
Clean and slice strawberries and put in cooled shell.
Pour cooled mixture over berries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: lasagna
directions: Mince garlic.
Combine all ingredients except cheeses and noodles.
Alternate layers of meat sauce, first, noodles, second and then cheeses (which have been cut fine or grated) in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beulah's lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and eggs.
Toss together flour and corn meal. Add to sugar and eggs.
Gradually add milk, melted butter, lemon juice, and rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
(Corn meal rises to form delicious crust over pie.)

title: poppy seed french bread
directions: Cut bread in 1 inch slices, not quite through the bottom. Mix all ingredients except Swiss cheese and spread mixture between each slice of bread.
Place slice of cheese between each slice of bread.
Spread top with any leftover margarine mixture.
Fold foil around bread leaving open at the top.
Heat in 350 degree oven for 25-30 minutes. Serves 10-12.

title: mystery bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Place soda crackers on cookie sheet.
Bring butter and brown sugar to rolling boil; stir and boil 3 minutes (no longer) or to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Pour over soda crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes (no longer).
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over mixture.
Spread as they melt.
Sprinkle with nuts; pat nuts into chocolate.
Refrigerate for 1 hour and break into pieces.
Keep in cookie can or Ziploc bags.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks.
Tastes like English toffee.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly, add garlic, parsley flakes, basil, salt, tomatoes, water and tomato paste to drained meat.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Combine cottage cheese with eggs, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Place layer of noodles on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Spread some cheese mix over noodles, then layer of meat, then some Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers until used up.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In a glass mixing bowl put margarine, oil, and marshmallows. Cook in microwave until melted. Pour over popcorn. Mix in nuts and M & M's. Put into angel food cake pan and let set for 30 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry together ground meat and onion until all pink disappears and onion is clear.
Add the enchilada sauce.
Mix together the soup, water and chilies (if used).
Break tortillas into several pieces.
In a 2-quart casserole, put a layer of tortillas, meat mixture, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight or all day.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Mix dry ingredients and combine with peaches.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and dot with margarine.
Bake at 400° about 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pork loin with muddy water marinade
directions: Mix marinade in a glass dish.
Add pork, turning to coat. Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning 3 to 4 times.
To grill: Use drip pan with 1 inch water.
Gas:
Medium/Low; place on grill over drip pan.
Cover, grill 30 minutes until it begins to brown. Turn and grill until 160 degrees.
Turn every 20 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before carving.

title: ice cream brownies
directions: Mix and bake brownies according to directions on the box. Cool and cut into squares.
Top with your favorite ice cream and chocolate sauce.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in hot oil in heavy pan, then remove chops.
Add onion, soup and milk to pan and blend with oil.
Set aside. Starting with potatoes, alternate layers of potatoes and cabbage into an 8-cup casserole.
Sprinkle each layer with flour; pour soup sauce over each layer.
Place chops on top and cover casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: orange waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and enough mayonnaise to cream and moisten.
Toss lightly and chill.
Serves six.

title: chocolate 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; press into a 13x9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: holiday coconut cake filling
directions: Blend yolks and sour cream in a medium, heavy saucepan.
Stir in sugar and cook over low heat, stirring until the mixture starts to simmer.
Simmer until thick.
Stir in other ingredients.

title: ice cream cake
directions: To make crust, combine crumbs, sugar and butter; mix well. Press onto bottom of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup finely chopped candies over crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool thoroughly; freeze.

title: souper chicken
directions: Mix soup and bouillon with milk.
Add rice and mushrooms and pour into large nonstick casserole pan.
Place chicken breasts in pan.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 384 calories, 3 grams fat.

title: jonamazetti
directions: Blend cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Place cooked noodles in greased casserole (9 x 12-inch).
Spread cheese mixture over noodles and pour meat sauce over top. Sprinkle shredded cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Chill 20 to 24 hours.

title: aunt helen's crunchy chicken
directions: Blend together cracker crumbs, parsley, salt, Parmesan cheese, garlic and black pepper.
Roll chicken in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place, skin side up, in casserole.
Cover with foil; bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Take foil off the last 15 minutes.
Great way to use stale Ritz crackers.

title: zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy; add sugar, vanilla, applesauce and zucchini.
Combine remaining ingredients and gently stir in. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch greased loaf pan or muffin pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 18 (1/2-inch) slices or 14 muffins.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Put margarine in baking dish and place in oven to melt while you mix sugar, flour, milk and egg. Pour this in middle of your baking dish over butter. Drain any can of fruit or berries. Spread on top of other mixture. Save juice drained from fruit to pour over cobbler after removing from oven. Cook at 400° until brown, about 15 or 20 minutes.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Mix all together as for bread dough.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Prebake crust at 375° until light brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Brown ground beef and/or Italian sausage.
Drain.
Pour one jar pizza sauce over crust and sprinkle the browned meat on top of that.
Add onions, mushrooms, black olives or whatever your favorite toppings are.
Top all with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for about 20 minutes in a 375° to 400° oven.
Joan suggests using any kind of meat or cheese you prefer.

title: lemon thyme chicken
directions: Measure flour, salt and pepper into large plastic bag.
Coat chicken in bag.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in olive oil. Chop onion; add butter and onion and cook.
Stir in remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes.
Place in a 13 x 9 inch glass dish and bake 350° for 40 minutes.
Add lemon and serve.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the butter, brown sugar and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, on ungreased baking sheet.
Dough will spread.
Bake for 11 to 13 minutes, or until set.
Yields 3 dozen Chewies.

title: spanish style string beans
directions: Saute
beef
and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil on medium-high heat.
Add bell pepper, onion, celery, carrots and beans; stir-fry for
minutes.
Add
tomato soup, tomato sauce and oregano flakes.
Add
water
is
sauce
is too thick.
Simmer until carrots and beans are tender.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in large pot.
Cook for 1 minute after it starts to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla to mixture.
Beat well.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Makes about 30 small cookies.

title: meringues cookies
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff. Gradually beat in sugar, salt, fold in vanilla and pecan pcs.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet; Bake at 275° for 40 min.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix well cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Put in pie crust and freeze.
Thaw before eating.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Line baking pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil or use a cooking bag.
Place roast in pan, in center of foil or bag.
Sprinkle all sides with onion soup mix.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup on top; seal in meat.
Bake at 350° for about 3 hours.
Remove meat to platter.
Skim off excess fat from meat juices.
Serves juices with meat or thicken to make a gravy.

title: spanish cream
directions: Scald milk with gelatin and sugar added.
Add egg yolks and cook until
mixture coats spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff. After removing custard from heat, fold in egg whites, salt and vanilla.
Pour into a dish to set.
Serve plain, with vanilla sauce or whipped cream.

title: chocolate and peanut butter cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tins with paper liners.
Put 1 tablespoon crumbs in bottom of each paper.
In small bowl, beat cream cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Beat in milk, then beat in eggs.
Divide mix in half.
Stir one half into melted chocolate. Repeat with peanut butter.
Put 2 tablespoons peanut butter mix in each cup.
Top with 2 tablespoons chocolate mix.

title: vegetable dill dip
directions: Mix in order given and stir.
Keep refrigerated.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix.
Pour 1/2 batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt butter and caramels; mix well.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk.
Sprinkle nut meats and chocolate chips onto baked cake.
Pour caramel mixture over all.
Add remaining mixture over the caramel mixture; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lemon sour cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt.
Slowly stir in 1 cup milk.
Cook and stir until mixture is boiling and thickened. Blend small amount of mixture into 3 slightly beaten egg yolks. Return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add 4 teaspoons butter, 1 teaspoon shredded lemon peel and 1/4 cup lemon juice. Cover and cool.
Fold in 1 cup dairy sour cream.
Spoon into baked 9-inch pastry shell.

title: old fashioned sugar cream pie(ewings restaurant)
directions: Pour all dry ingredients into pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour wet ingredients over dry ingredients and mix with your fingertips until free of lumps.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast in water.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, butter and flour.
Stir until well mixed.
Roll dough out on lightly floured surface in shape of pan.
Sprinkle pan lightly with cornmeal.
Put dough on pan and place in a warm place until dough doubles in size, anywhere from 40 minutes to 2 hours.
Add your toppings and cook about 30 minutes, or until crust is brown.

title: double chocolate crumble bars
directions: Mix ingredients together, then bake at 350°F until bars test done.
Add 2 c. marshmallows on top of bars and bake 3 more min. Melt 1 ppkg. chocolate chips and 1 c. peanut butter on oven.
Mix together with 1 1/2 c. Rice Krispies and spread on top of marshmallows and let cool.
Keep it in the fridge for a better taste.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Prepare spaghetti sauce as directed.
Mix noodles, sauce and soup.
Pour into baking pan and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts thoroughly.

title: hot crab sandwich
directions: Slice loaves of bread in half lengthwise and set aside. Combine next 7 ingredients and spread on bread halves.
Top with slices of Swiss cheese and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
May garnish with nuts before serving. Yields 6 sandwiches.

title: refrigerator all-bran muffins
directions: Scald 1 cup All-Bran in boiling water; add raisins (if desired).
Add this to sugar, 2 cups All-Bran, shortening, eggs, flour and salt in a large bowl.
Mix in other bowl, buttermilk and soda; mix well.
Add to other ingredients.
Add raisins and bran; beat this well but only by hand.
Put in airtight container.
Put in refrigerator.
Don't stir again.
When you want muffins, use cupcake baking shells.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Return remaining batter to refrigerator until needed.

title: zucchini nut bread(yields 2 loaves)
directions: In a bowl, place flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Toss lightly with a fork to mix.
In large bowl, beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Add zucchini, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts.
Spread batter in a well buttered 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until bread tests done, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool bread in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on racks.
Don't cut until completely cool.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs, sugar and cinnamon.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter; add to crumbs.
Butter pan bottom and sides.
Press mix.

title: biscuits
directions: Measure dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Cut milk into flour mixture until meal like texture is formed.
Add milk and mix until smooth.
Roll out on floured board or between two pieces of wax paper to 1/2-inch thickness; cut into biscuits and bake on oil baking pan at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These make great shortcake biscuits.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: While cake is hot, punch holes in it and pour
milk evenly all over.
Prepare jello with only 1/2 of water required on package. Pour over cake.
Add strawberries.
Ice with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: microwave granola
directions: Place oats in 2-quart dish.
Heat on Full powder for 1 to 2 1/2 minutes or until warmed.
Stir twice during heating time.
Add remaining ingredients to oats.
Stir until mixture is well coated.

title: taco stuffed peppers
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add taco seasoning, beans and salsa. Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise; clean.
Blanch 3 minutes; drain.
Spoon meat mixture in peppers. Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with tomato, cheese and sour cream.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Put 1 or 2 teaspoons in each cup.
Add cold or hot water.
Nice to put in jars and give as gifts for any occasion.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Mix well.
Add other ingredients. Bake in a tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecued onions
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onion, in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in onion.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Cover and chill.
Serve with vegetables or barbecue meats.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: happy day
directions: Will make a great day for anyone you happen to meet.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and continue to beat. Add chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
It is important to beat well after each addition.
Fold in pecans, if desired.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.

title: kansas dirt
directions: Crush cookies; layer 1/2 in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth; add powdered sugar.
Fold in whipped topping.
In separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in cheese mixture and pudding.
Pour into pan and sprinkle cookie crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions. Cool and crumble.
In large bowl combine cornbread, tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, celery, mayonnaise and dash or two of Tabasco sauce.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese cake tarts
directions: Whip cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy. Put a vanilla wafer in each cupcake paper-lined muffin pan.
Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with pie filling and top with whipped topping if you like.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pour 1/2 batter in baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and peppers.
Pour balance of batter on top and again top with grated cheese and peppers.
Bake in a slow oven (about 375°) for 45 minutes or more.

title: anna's sausage rolls
directions: Mix flour, buttermilk and butter.
Roll out on floured surface.
Put sausage on dough.
Roll it up.
Cut into 1/4-inch pieces.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in grits.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter, eggs, salt, seasoned salt, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Mix grated cheese with other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: green spinach pie
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine until tender.
Stir in spinach.
Remove from heat.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli just until tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Garnish the top with another boiled egg, quartered, and pimentos if desired.

title: praline cookies
directions: Put sugar through strainer.
Add flour, salt and rum.
Fold in egg white, then pecans.
Bake, on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam, at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and shortening.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder and sugar; add to egg mixture and beat smooth.
Add potatoes and onion and blend well.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Makes 12 to 15 pancakes.

title: potluck pan rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and 1 tsp. sugar in 1/2 C. water.
Add butter, eggs, milk powder, salt, 3 C. flour and remaining sugar and water.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes or until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 - 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes until brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set in refrigerator for at least an hour before serving with assorted vegetables.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until firm.

title: no cook vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating until mixture thickens.
Freeze in freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut cheese from corner to corner, to make 2 triangles from each slice.
Roll out each biscuit individually on wax paper. Place 1 triangle of cheese and 1/2 hot dog on rolled out dough; roll up.
Make sure you seal tightly by pinching dough together at both ends.
Heat oven to 450°; bake for 15 minutes at 450° or until golden brown.

title: cheese straws
directions: Let butter and cheese stand at room temperature for 2 hours. Cream together thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Fill cookie press.
Form straws on ungreased cookie sheet, using star plate.
Cut across strips making each about 3 or 4 inches long.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
Best if served a day old.
Will keep a week or more.

title: noodles supreme
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook carrot and onion in margarine over medium heat about 3 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add water, soup, mushrooms and pepper; stir well and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and return to slow boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add broccoli and continue to cook 10 more minutes or until broccoli and noodles are tender, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add mushroom juice to broth and cook noodles in this.
Do not drain noodles.
In 2 tablespoons of chicken fat or butter, saute green pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Add this to chicken.
To cooked noodles, add soup and next 6 ingredients.
In greased 3-quart casserole, place 1 layer of noodle mixture, then one of chicken mixture.
Alternate with noodles on top.
Sprinkle with almond chips.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Do not cover.

title: quick and delicious halibut
directions: Place halibut ina baking dish and pour dressing over the top to coat the fillet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients; add to Cheddar cheese and shrimp.
Serve on crackers.

title: sweet and sour meatballs or waikiki meatballs
directions: *I usually double this recipe so there is enough gravy.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Mix all ingredients and let stand overnight.
In the morning, pack into sterilized jars and seal.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Mix condensed milk with lemon juice.
Beat whipped cream very stiff.
Fold into milk mixture.
Add strawberries and nuts.
Line dish with half of vanilla wafers and pour mixture into dish.
Top with rest of vanilla wafers.
Chill and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup. Mix in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will also need a flowerpot.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice; drain and rinse.
Saute peppers and onions until tender.
Add sausage and cook until brown.
Mix ingredients together.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Salt and pepper.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter real well.
Add sugar and cream.
Add beaten egg. Measure and sift dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine molasses and hot water.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture alternately with liquid, a small amount at a time, and beat after each addition until smooth.

title: sandy's broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: Combine ingredients and let simmer for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and egg yolks, stirring well.
Add milk, cranberries and flour.
Before stirring, add baking powder. Pour into 9-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until heated through and cheese is melted, 5 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dr. two trees' cure for diabetes(old fort, north carolina, native american indian)
directions: Wash bananas.
Boil 20 minutes in 2-quarts of water.
Strain and store in glass (not plastic) container in refrigerator.
Drink 1 quart a day for 6 weeks.
Will be cured and back to normal.

title: horseradish dip
directions: Mix together well and serve.

title: king alphonse
directions: Mix water, coffee and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved. Cool to room temperature.
Add whiskey and split vanilla bean lengthwise and cut into small pieces.
Place in large jar and store in dark place 10 days.
Shake once a day.
Serve in small glass with a little cream on top.

title: dinner in a crust
directions: Cook beef, onion and celery, stirring to crumble beef; drain off drippings.
Stir in next 7 ingredients and spoon into pastry shells.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cut cheese in halves diagonally and arrange 6 halves on each pie.
Return to oven 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Top pies with tomato sauce.

title: barbecued green beans
directions: Brown onion in small amount of bacon grease.
Add ketchup, brown sugar, and Worcestershire sauce; simmer for 2 minutes; then add bacon pieces.
Place green beans in casserole dish.
Pour sauce mixture over top - do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Pour filling into crust and cook about 30 minutes, or until pie is set, at 350°.
Place thawed strawberries and 1 tablespoon flour in pan and cook until thick.
Pour in lemon juice.
Cool and spread over cooled pie.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken with onion and celery stalks.
Remove chicken and debone.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Mix chicken pieces, spaghetti, onion, celery, canned vegetables, bell pepper and soup. Season to taste.
If you like, add 4 ounces grated cheese.
Mix and place in casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.
Freezes well.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey and wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Saute onions in margarine.
Remove from heat and stir in flour.
Drain mushrooms and save liquid.
Combine that liquid with cream and enough liquids to make 4 cups.
Stir slowly into flour mixture. Cook and stir until thick.
Add rice, mushrooms, turkey, toasted almonds, pimiento, parsley, salt and pepper.
Put in a 9x13-inch pan, and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: smothered steak
directions: Combine flour, pepper and salt.
Pound into steak with mallet. Brown steak in large skillet containing the shortening.
Add soup and water.
Cover; cook over low heat about 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: grandma lydia's german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skin and a little salt.
Peel and slice. Add onion, chopped bacon and pepper to potatoes.
Heat half of bacon fat, butter and flour (mixed with a little water until smooth), 1 1/2 cups water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil until thick.
Pour over potatoes and stir.
Serve warm.
May be prepared earlier and heated before serving.
Reheats in microwave especially well.

title: zucchini squash nut bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Incorporate evenly. Store in airtight container.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine eggs, sweet potatoes, sugar, salt and spices. Gradually add evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking about 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center of pie comes out clean.
Cool before serving; garnish as desired.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Mix with soups and water. Put in a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle bread stuffing over this mixture; pour butter over it.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: taco spread dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sour cream together in a 10-inch pie plate and spread in plate.
Spread taco sauce on top of cheese mixture, then cheese and finally top with tomatoes and peppers. Chill and serve with tacos.

title: honey-sour cream dip
directions: Combine sour cream, honey and cinnamon in bowl; mix well. Serve as dip or salad dressing with assorted fresh fruit.
Yields 20 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Do not drain.
In medium pan, heat all other ingredients, except rice, until well blended.
Add broccoli and rice.
Place in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: the best new york firehouse chili
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown ground meat and sausage.
Transfer to a 4-quart pot.
In the same skillet, add beef stock and bring to a boil.
Remove stock from heat.
Crumble saffron and add to stock.
Set this aside.

title: frittata
directions: Heat oil and cook vegetables until crisp and tender.
Beat eggs, cream, salt, pepper and thyme.
Stir in vegetables, bread, Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Spray with Pam or butter a quiche pan or 8 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: meat balls
directions: In large pan, start heating tomato juice.
In large bowl, mix hamburger meat with your usual taste amount of salt and pepper.
In small bowl, put flour.
Get small amount of hamburger and fashion into a ball.
Roll in flour, then press flour onto ball.
Put in boiling tomato juice.
Cook, stirring often, until done, about 20 minutes.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Stir buttermilk into beaten eggs.
Add 1/4 cup bacon drippings. Combine all dry ingredients.

Add to liquid ingredients all at once, then sprinkle the crumbled bacon into the batter. Beat well and pour into a large pan (9 x 12-inch) or heavy iron skillet (12-inch); bake until golden brown in the hot oven. Cut into wedges or squares and serve hot.

title: bubbles
directions: Combine and shake.
Let set 4 hours.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Cook 1 package wild rice according to the instructions on package.
Mix together cooked wild rice, crabmeat, mushroom soup, milk and the cheese.
Put all ingredients into a casserole.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Thank God for dirty dishes.

title: grits casserole
directions: Combine grits, water and salt.
Cook until grits are done. Add butter; stir until melted.
Add cheese, and melt.
Beat eggs in a teacup, and finish filling with milk.
Add this mixture to grits.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix until cake icing consistency, then spread on 3 slices of bread and stack.
Cut bread in four sections.
Ice sides and top (not the bottom).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: green beans and tomatoes
directions: Cut off tips of beans. Drop beans into boiling salted water; return to boil. Simmer about 5 minutes (crisp-tender). Do not overcook. Drain.

title: chocolate pecan crunch pie
directions: Add sugar to eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 250° to 275° or until filling is set.
Serve with whipped cream toppings or ice cream.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook 1 hour or until thickened.
Serve with spaghetti and meat balls.

title: apple snack cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well mixed.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in pecans, half of butterscotch morsels and apples.
Spread batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Sprinkle batter with remaining morsels.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage in skillet.
Drain and set aside.
Separate dough into 8 triangles, arrange on ungreased 12 - inch pizza pan, points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust, sealing completely.
Spoon sausage over crust, sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheddar cheese; set aside.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, and pepper in a mixing bowl, mix well.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all together, except granulated sugar.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar and place, sugar side up, 3 inches apart on lightly greased sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: family favorite
directions: Mix jello and water.
Cool.
Mix cottage cheese, Miracle Whip and coffee cream; blend.
Add grated carrot and green pepper (and onion, if desired).
Refrigerate until solid.

title: schifnoodle
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops over medium heat.
Place cabbage, onion, carrots, potatoes and green pepper over pork chops. Pour water and tomatoes over vegetables.
Cover.
Bring to a full boil; reduce heat to low.
Cook until vegetables are tender (30 to 45 minutes).
Place bread dough over vegetables.
Cover; continue cooking until bread is no longer doughy (20 to 25 minutes).
Do not remove cover until ready to serve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Pick over and discard bones in salmon.
Add bread crumbs, eggs and next 6 ingredients.
Mix together.
Put in loaf tin.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with Hollandaise Sauce.

title: cinnamon salad
directions: Dissolve candies in boiling water; add jello, stirring until dissolved.	Chill until partially set.
Fold in applesauce.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch dish and chill until firm.
Cream remaining ingredients together and spread over gelatin mixture.
Grate a little cheese over top for garnish.

title: fluffy lime dessert
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter and stir in graham cracker crumbs.
Pat firmly in 11 x 7 pan; chill.
In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in sweetened milk, pineapple and lemon juice.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Pour in prepared pan. Chill for two hours.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix together the sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add boiling water and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and lemon juice. Cool.
Serve over pudding or cake.

title: humentashen(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Chill dough 20 minutes.

title: friendly garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F.
Separate garlic into cloves.
In a saucepan of rapidly boiling water, blanch garlic for about 30 seconds.
Run garlic under cold water.
Trim tops and bottom of garlic and slip off skins.
Pour olive oil into a 3-4 quart casserole dish with tightly fitting lid.
Add garlic and toss to coat with oil.
Add chicken and turn to coat with oil.
Scatter parsley over top and sprinkle with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Put half in mold and freeze for 30 minutes.
Spread 8 ounces of sour cream over jello; pour remaining jello mixture on top.
Refrigerate.

title: glazed carrots (4)
directions: Wash, scrape and cut carrots into 1 1/2-inch sticks.
Cook in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Add butter, sugar, salt and mint or parsley; cook over medium heat until glazed.

title: coconut sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix, according to directions.
Split layers when cool.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut, blending well. (Chill.)
Reserve 1 cup of mixture for frosting; spread remainder between layers of cake.
Combine the reserved cup of mixture with whipped topping; blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Seal cake in airtight container and refrigerate 3 days.

title: slivered pork, vegetables, pasta
directions: Preheat oven 375°.
Cook pasta to package directions.
Drain and return to pot.
Add 1 teaspoon of the oil and toss to coat. Heat remaining 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium heat Add pork and cook until browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add bell pepper, onion, mushrooms, garlic, oregano, and thyme.
Cook until onion is almost soft, 6 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in crushed tomatoes, and cook 5 minutes.
Season with the salt and pepper.
Add to pasta, tossing to combine.
Pour into shallow 2 1/2 or 3 quart baking dish.
Top with tomato (only around the edges if desired), and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until heated through and cheese is melted and slightly browned, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked fruit
directions: Grease with margarine an oblong baking dish.
Place ingredients in baking dish in given order.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: glenn's favorite harvest oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add oatmeal.
Grind raisins and add boiling water to soften.
Mix in cinnamon, salt, soda and flour.
Let stand overnight.

title: turkey in a sack
directions: You will also need 1 large, brown grocery bag (heavy-duty type).

title: no bake cookies
directions: Microwave butter and milk for 1 minute.
Add sugar and cocoa, mixing well.
Microwave for 3 minutes or to boiling.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add vanilla and salt.
Stir in peanut butter and oats. Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: cheese ball(quick)
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix together to form a ball and roll in nuts.
Use with either crackers or carrots and celery.

title: cheese strata
directions: Spread trimmed bread with softened butter.
Cut each slice into 4 strips.
Butter a 2-quart casserole and make alternate layers of bread strips, sausage or chopped ham and grated cheese, ending with the cheese.
Beat eggs.
Add seasonings and milk. Pour over top cheese layer and refrigerate for at least 24 hours, covered.
Take out of refrigerator for an hour or so before baking so that it comes to room temperature.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Sprinkle with paprika and chopped parsley before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fettucini with shellfish
directions: Put butter and oil in skillet over medium heat until butter melts and mixture bubbles.
Add wine, garlic, rosemary, oregano and onion.
Cook, stirring until wine evaporates and butter is golden.
Reduce heat and add tomatoes.
Cook until heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add shellfish, parsley, sugar and salt and pepper.
Stir until shellfish is heated through and serve over hot pasta.
Serves 6.

title: cinnamon toast(kids)
directions: Toast bread.
Spread butter.
Shake on cinnamon/sugar mixture. Cut into triangles.
Eat and share with your brother and sister.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Sift flour.
Add to egg with cream.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased tube cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry nut cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour and other ingredients.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° by dropping by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Nice for Christmas.

title: cake - cookie
directions: Mix together the melted butter, brown sugar and flour until crumbly.
Set aside 2/3 to 1 cup for the topping.
To the remainder, add the egg, baking soda, salt, milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumbs and top with layer of chocolate chips or chopped nuts if desired. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: apple salad
directions: Stir to mix and serve.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Blend the 1 cup flour and confectioners sugar in a bowl.
Cut in the butter until blended.
Firmly and evenly press into an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, combine sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and baking powder. Blend into beaten eggs, along with lemon juice.
Pour mixture over crust.
Return to oven and bake 25 minutes.
Remove to wire rack and cool.
Glaze with a thin confectioners sugar icing.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt on low heat or in microwave the cheese and margarine, stirring well.
Add sugar and cocoa to melted margarine.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover and refrigerate.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: purple cows(rich grape drink)
directions: In blender container, combine milk, frozen juice concentrates and ice cream.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve in tall glasses with straws.
Garnish with whipped dessert topping and mint leaves, if desired.
Serves 1 or 2.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, take off bone and dice.
Mix soup, sour cream and diced chicken.
Follow directions on Stove Top stuffing.
Spread over chicken dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and place in a tightly covered container.
Add by teaspoon to hot water, suited to taste, usually 2 teaspoons to 6 ounces hot water.
Good anytime, especially on a cold winter day.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.

title: boiled chiamele
directions: Make a well into the flour, add eggs and beat well with a wire whisk.
Add sugar and oil and keep beating with whisk, gradually scraping in the flour.
When all the flour is absorbed, knead dough until well blended.
Roll dough out and form like doughnut rings.
Put rings into boiling water and boil until they raise to the top of water.
