Take out of water one at a time and put on dish towel to dry.
Cut slits around rings.
Bake on oven grates at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 10 more minutes until golden brown.

title: slow cooker dressing
directions: Place 1 corny joke between 2 old war stories.
Squash together.
Should last 20 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together.
Store in an airtight container.
Use 3 teaspoons for each cup of tea.

title: pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans in pie shell.
In large bowl beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over pecans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rum cake
directions: Cake:
Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix and pudding.
Add remaining ingredients; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, until tested done.
Carefully loosen edges with a dull knife.
Leave in pan.
Prick cake with a fork to absorb glaze.
Pour glaze over hot cake.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Invert onto a serving plate.

title: buttermilk cinnamon swirl bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, soda and salt. In another bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs and buttermilk; mix well. Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fill two greased 8 x 4 or five 5 x 2 loaf pans about one-third full. Combine swirl ingredients; sprinkle half of the mixture over the batter. Top with remaining batter, then remaining cinnamon sugar. Swirl batter with a knife. Bake at 350° for 45 - 55 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pans for about 10 minutes before turning onto a wire rack.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
boiling water; drain pineapple and measure
liquid.
Add water to make 1 cup.	Add to jello, stir in cranberry
sauce
and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan. Refrigerate
until	firm.
Combine	cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.	Spread on congealed salad.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make well in center of mixture.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake, as long as 5 to 6 weeks.
When ready, spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: french fried zucchini squash
directions: Beat eggs slightly with fork.
Slice squash in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Dip in egg and then in crumbs.
Fry in deep fat, 350°, until golden brown, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown turkey sausage in oil.
Mix crumbled sausage, beans and taco sauce into casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Chop onion and pepper.
Cream cottage cheese with electric beater until smooth.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dip cauliflower, celery sticks and carrot strips into this dip.

title: molasses pound cake
directions: Butter and flour a loaf pan.
Set the oven at 350°.
Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, milk and molasses. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, allspice, ground cloves and mace. Add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and citron. Spoon into the pan and bake about 40 minutes.

title: white bread
directions: In a large bowl thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine water, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat to 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1 cup flour or enough to make a thick batter. Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix
all ingredients an put in buttered casserole.
Dot top with butter (1 tablespoon).
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered,
in
400° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 5
minutes
longer.
Makes 8 servings.
Each serving contains 145 calories, 40 grams protein and 4.1 grams of fat.

title: john's mix-up
directions: Spread slice of bread with peanut butter.
Slice dill pickle lengthwise; place on peanut butter.
Spread mayonnaise on other slice of bread.
Put slices together and enjoy.

title: butter balls
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and vanilla together until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour.
Form dough into balls and roll each ball in sugar.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Beat egg and add to milk.
Add meal and flour; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling stock of turnip greens.
Cook until dumpling rises to top and is done.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream eggs, brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Add and mix well; corn syrup, soda, butter and peanut butter.
Add oatmeal, chocolate chips and M&M's.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jeannine's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together above ingredients.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in preheated oven.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine in large saucepan sugar, flour and cornstarch.
Add to this butter, milk and slightly beaten yolks of the eggs.
Add salt and place over medium heat.
Place 1/2 cup sugar in a large iron skillet over medium heat.
Stir first mixture frequently while you keep an eye on the sugar in skillet, but don't stir.
As soon as the custard mixture begins to cook slightly, stir constantly until it reaches a rolling boil.
By this time the sugar in the skillet should have begun to melt.
When almost all has melted, stir well. It should be caramelized and bubbly all over.
Now add the custard and mix well, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth, creamy and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Pour caramel mixture in 2 baked 9-inch pastry shells and bake meringue.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix the Sugar with the Eggs.
Sift the Flour, Cornmeal, Baking Powder, and Salt together.
Add the melted Butter and Milk.
Stir in the Egg mixture.
Beat quickly by hand (do not use an electric mixer, which will give the cornbread the texture of cake).
Bake in a 9 by 11 inch buttered pan in a 350 oven for 20 - 25 minutes. Makes 21 squares.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Marinate beef tenderloin in dry white wine for 2 hours or so. Brush meat with sweet butter and sprinkle 3/4 cup caraway seed over meat.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons over meat and roast for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Saute mushrooms in sweet butter.
Add 1 cup of marinade and a lot of chopped parsley.
Add the juice from the pan. Slice meat and pour the sauce over it.

title: 7-cup salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. In medium bowl, with wooden spoon, beat egg.
Gradually beat in 2/3 cup sugar and beat until well combined.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to sugar mixture, alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in blueberries. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle top with 2 tablespoons of sugar. Bake 25 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched. Serve warm with butter.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill until ready to serve.

title: stroganoff
directions: Freeze meat until just firm.
Slice into thin strips and brown. Saute onion and mushrooms.
Add brown gravy mix with water (may use 2 packages, if more juice is desired).
Cook until tender (about 20 minutes).
Add sour cream 10 minutes before serving. Heat until hot; do not boil. Serve over homemade style noodles.

title: honey almond cheesecake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add cream cheese and cream until fluffy.
Blend in flour and honey, then egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add half and half and extract, then lightly fold in egg whites.
Fold in the almonds with a few strokes.
Pour into greased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour. Turn off oven and cool in oven with door closed for 1 hour. Remove from pan and chill.
Add topping of your choice or leave plain.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Blend flour, milk and butter in bowl.
Mix well.
Roll out on slightly floured wax paper.
Cut with cutter.
Place on slightly oiled pan.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.

title: vegetable noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Saute celery, onion, green pepper and broccoli in oil until tender.
Stir in milk and next 3 ingredients.
Add noodles and spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Scramble ground beef until brown.
Place in casserole dish. Slice potatoes and onions and place on top of ground beef.
Add cream of mushroom soup; do not stir.
Cook in 325° oven for 1 hour or until the potatoes are done.
Remove from oven.
Top with eggs.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter 2 slices bread.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes and set aside. Cut remaining slices into 1-inch cubes.
Place half of unbuttered cubes in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: coffee bake
directions: Preheat Oven 350° Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients starting with the eggs.
Mix well.
Grease and flour Angel Food Cake pan.
Mix TOPPING:
1 cup sugar, 2 tsp. Cinnamon and 3\4 cup chopped walnuts.
Pour 1\2 batter into pan. Spread topping over batter, evenly.
Add remaining batter.
Top with remaining topping.
Bake for 45 min.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Pour milk into a deep mixer bowl.
Add pudding and Dream Whip; beat on low speed until blended.
Beat on high until soft peaks form (4 to 6 minutes).
Store frosted cake or cupcakes in refrigerator.

title: brownies
directions: Melt Crisco and cocoa together and set aside to cool.
Beat eggs slightly.
Blend in sugar.
Add chocolate mixture and stir well.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture and stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot apple-tang
directions: Heat liquids, then add Tang and spices.
Serve piping hot.

title: italian salad
directions: Mix Italian dressing and Parmesan cheese together.
Add to vegetables and pasta.
Great summer salad!

title: millet butter
directions: Cook agar-agar flakes in water for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring. Blenderize 1/2 of cooked agar-agar with other ingredients until very smooth.
Add rest of the agar-agar, blending at low speed. Cool a little and put in serving dishes to finish cooling.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease	9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple, coconut, cake mix, margarine and
nuts
in
that order.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gosh that's good
directions: Brown beef; add celery and onion and brown slightly.
Add tomato sauce and cheese.
Cook on low heat about 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni in salted water; drain.
Add to meat mixture; add tomatoes.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Add tomato juice if mixture dries a bit while baking.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add
eggs,
brandy and nutmeg. Sift 2 1/2 cups flour and
soda.
Add
fruit
and
nuts, mixed with remaining 1/2 cup flour.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ever ready salad dressing
directions: Mix together thoroughly by shaking in a quart jar.

title: everyday meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, ground beef, onions and bread crumbs in large mixing bowl.
Stir in milk, salt, pepper, catsup and mustard. Mix ingredients well.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Heat to boiling over medium heat and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add baking soda and salt.
Pour over popcorn until evenly coated.
Mix well.

title: ah so
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Melt butter in large baking dish.
Add soy sauce, garlic and salt, mixing well.
Add noodles and nuts; coat well.
Spread mixture evenly in dish.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until crisp.

title: pioneer beans
directions: Put all ingredients in large sauce pan and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer on low for 2 - 3 hrs.
Add water if necessary.
Very Good!

title: tofu balls
directions: Mix well; form into golf ball sized rounds.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When ready to serve, place frozen balls into baking dish; cover with sauce and cover.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: celery apple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Add cinnamon candies to 1 cup boiling water; stir to liquid.
Add to dissolved gelatin. Cool until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: love at first bite
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix flour, pecans and margarine.
Press into bottom of long pan. Cook at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown. Cool.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix in bowl with mixer or by hand until very smooth.
Spread in a glass casserole dish.
Add chopped lettuce and tomato on top. Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve with tacos.

title: cinnamon pecan crunch
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add pecan halves. Toss and coat all nuts with egg white mixture.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Pour over wet nuts.
Coat well and pour on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and remove from cookie sheet immediately.

title: gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: You will also need nonstick spray coating.

title: lasagne
directions: Combine meat and spaghetti sauce.
Combine cheeses and eggs. Place small amount of meat sauce mixture in ovenware bowl.
Place a layer of egg-cheese mixture over meat sauce.
Add a layer of noodles.
Continue alternating layers of meat sauce, cheese mixture and noodles, ending with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Add mayonnaise when ready to serve.
Chill.

title: creamed hominy
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan. Let come to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes or until cream thickens.

title: alma's "nassau" wings(new providence island cuisine)
directions: Place cleaned, disjointed wings in foil-lined 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with seasonings on both sides.
In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over wings and bake, uncovered, turning and basting with sauce every 15 minutes.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°.
Serves 10 to 12 as appetizer or 6 to 8 as main dish.

title: spicy candied walnuts
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Stir a few minutes.
Lift nuts from syrup with fork, separate them and allow to dry on waxed paper.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
Reserve trunk; you'll need some place to store the pieces.
Add enough gravy to cover. Cook over fire for two months at 4650°.
This will serve 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, more rabbits can be added, but most people don't like hare in their soup.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls of mix per cup of boiling water.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook stuffing according to package directions and put in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, then put chicken and eggs on top of stuffing.
Mix all other ingredients and spread on top.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and water.
Cook 5 minutes or until clear.
Remove from heat and add lemon juice.
Stretch each biscuit into a 4-inch circle.
Place diced apples in the center and dot with butter.
Gather up dough and "pinch" together at the top.
Place in baking dish.
Pour syrup over dumplings and bake for 25 minutes.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and clear. Remove from heat.
Add jello (straight from the package) and cool.

title: chocolate boats
directions: Prepare 6 boat shaped containers out of heavy-duty foil.
Make them about 5 inches long with the sides about 1-inch high.
Stack 5 wafers with jam in between each.
Lay stack on its side in the boat.
Gently separate wafers enough to place 1 marshmallow and a few chocolate chips between each two wafers.
Grill over a low flame for about 10 minutes, until chocolate melts and marshmallows soften.

title: conga bars
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Set oven to 375°.
Cream the margarine.
Add the sugar gradually. Add one egg at a time, beating constantly. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add a little at a time.
Beat in vanilla, chocolate and nuts. Spread evenly in pan. Bake for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting. Makes 24 to 30 pieces.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Melt stick of margarine. Add flour. Stir until blended.
Add nuts in pie pan to make the shell.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Just mix all ingredients together and refrigerate maybe 1-2 hours (sometimes not necessary if your Cool Whip is still frozen) and serve. Very cool and simple dessert.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Cook sugar, milk, chocolate and salt over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Beat. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.

title: shrimp mold for dip
directions: Pour gelatine into warm soup.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise and pour remaining ingredients into oiled mold.
Chill overnight.

title: sunshine pickles
directions: Add the dill, garlic cloves and salt to the cucumbers.
Fill gallon jar with water.
Put a crust of bread on top.
Put lid on and sit in sun for 7 days.
After 7 days, rinse in cold water several times.
Mix the remaining ingredients.
Do not heat.
Just stir in bowl.
Pour over cucumbers in jar.
Keep shaking jar to mix pickles.
Can be eaten after 3 days.

title: watergate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cream dip
directions: Mix together well.
May place on low in microwave to assist mixture in softening and to allow mixture to blend smoother.
Dip is used with any type of fruit.
The simplest recipe, but tastes like a million dollars!

title: fiesta salad
directions: Brown meat; drain well.
Saute onions, add to meat.
Add all of the other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Arrange and serve in the following way (buffet style) and do not let your guests skip any steps:

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook and cube chicken.
Reserve 1 cup of broth.
Melt butter; add onion and celery.
Saute until tender.
Add soup, chicken and 1 cup of broth.
Stir and simmer.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook noodles until they're almost soft and drain.
Add soup mixture and stir.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: whoopee pies
directions: Add flour to cake mix.
Mix as directed on box.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done (8 to 10 minutes).
Cool.

title: fresh vegetable marinade 2
directions: Mix together last 6 ingredients. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cake
directions: Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 55 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Use a Duncan Hines cake mix.
Do as directed; cool and split the layers in half.
Ice and put in Tupperware cake cover.
Seal and let stay in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop from spoon to make small bite-size pieces of dough.
Bake 18 minutes at 375°.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Break corned beef in small pieces.
Add chicken soup, 1/2 cup milk, minced onion, cooked macaroni and cheese, cut in small pieces.
Place in medium-size casserole and sprinkle crushed potato chips over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sour cream frosting
directions: Combine nuts,
sugar and sour cream and bring to a boil. Reduce heat
and
cook
slowly
for
15 minutes or until thick. When thick,
add
the well beaten egg white and mix thoroughly. Allow mixture
to
cool.
Spread
between
layers and to top of cake.
(Not sufficient amount to cover sides of cake, but since it is so rich, it really doesn't need to.)

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars.
Add egg, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Form into logs and freeze overnight.
Slice and bake at 325° to 350° for 10 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: georgia cracker salad
directions: Crush crackers.
Mix all ingredients together and serve immediately.
Mix in mayonnaise right before serving.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Grease skillet and preheat.
Squeeze spinach dry.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into hot skillet and cook at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and milk.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in cream.
Layer pudding, wafers and bananas.

title: aunt mary's pound cake
directions: Let butter soften.
Mix butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time while mixing.
Sift baking powder, flour and salt together, then add slowly while mixing.
Add vanilla.
Preheat oven and start at 300°.
Bake for 45 minutes, then decrease oven heat to 250° and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fat-free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheets. Bake 10 minutes until firm.
Do not overbake!
Remove from pan and cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Combine hamburger, sausage, rice and onion.
Mix well.
Roll in cabbage leaves.
Place in a 9
x 13-inch pan.
Top with tomato sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in tightly closed jars.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
To cooked, drained pasta add butter, cheese, and evaporated milk. Toss to mix; serve immediately.
Makes 6 one-cup servings.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: In skillet saute beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, breaking up beef with fork.
Stir in the flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in bouillon and mushrooms and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened and boils.
Reduce heat; stir in sour cream.
Cook 5 minutes (do not boil).
Serve over noodles (I prefer rice).
Serves 4.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix shortening and peel.
Add flour slowly.
Add crumbs, spices, sugar and eggs.
Put into pudding cloth.
Wrap coins in wax paper and bury in pudding.
Drop into kettle of boiling water. Boil 5 to 7 hours.
Serve with Brandy Hard sauce.

title: creamy punch
directions: Mix ice cream, sherbet and a touch of limeade in large punch bowl.
When the mixture is somewhat soft, then finish mixing in the rest of the ingredients.

title: apple cake with rum sauce
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Add beaten eggs and diced apples.
Sift and add dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and nuts. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or two smaller, such as 8 x 8-inch, in 350° oven for one hour.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Boil raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes.
Add Crisco; cool.
Add 1 cup water.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Add baking soda.
Flour and grease pans.
Makes 2 square or loaf pans or 1 Bundt and loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Beat by hand.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Optional:
add raisins, nuts, dates or applesauce.)

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Melt oleo and saute bell pepper.
Add pimento, salt and pepper.
Add flour and blend until thickened.
Add milk and cook until sauce begins to thicken.
Add cheese and cook on low until melted.
Place potatoes in a single layer in a large baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Pour blended cheese sauce over potatoes and bake 45 minutes at 350° uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini bars
directions: In large saucepan, heat the butter or margarine, water and brown sugar.
Beat well.
Remove from the heat and beat in the egg and vanilla.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Makes 15 to 18 servings.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: swedish slaw
directions: Shred 5 to 6 pounds of cabbage and sprinkle 1 cup of sugar over it; set to one side.

title: pork chop and sweet potato casserole for 2
directions: Slice potatoes crosswise into 1/4-inch thickness.
Place in buttered 1 quart casserole dish.
Dot with the butter and sprinkle with the salt and pepper.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cut up potatoes.
Add rest of ingredients. Cover and cook 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: doves on the grill
directions: Salt and pepper to taste breasts of doves.
Wrap each individually with a slice of bacon; secure with toothpicks. Place on grill and cook until done.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add milk and cook over double broiler.
Spoon some of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Add to pie filling along with butter and flavoring.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: filbert yams
directions: Mix honey, margarine, mace and lemon juice.
Slice oranges and arrange between slices of yams in a greased baking dish.
Spread honey mixture over top.
Scatter chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Good with pork or ham.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: cereal-nut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: waffles
directions: Mix ingredients together but do not overbeat.
Pour desired amount into waffle iron.
Enjoy!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni in 2 qt. saucepan.
Drain when tender.
Cook cubed velveeta cheese, margarine and milk over low heat until melted and sauce is smooth.
Add macaroni, salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes on low heat.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine cans of corn, eggs and sour cream in a large bowl. In a cup, mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to corn.
Prepare cornbread mix according to the box.
Add to corn mixture and stir well.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake in 325° oven until browned and firm.

title: white bread
directions: Scald milk; add Crisco, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Add milk mixture and egg; add enough flour to make soft dough.
Beat with mixer until dough looks elastic.
By hand, add enough flour to make stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl; turn and grease top.
With kitchen fork, punch 8 holes in the dough.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 2 hours.
Shape dough into 3 loaves. Brush tops with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until doubled. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked potato(microwave)
directions: Prick potatoes twice with a fork.
Place a layer of paper towels on the oven floor.
Arrange potatoes at least 1 inch apart.

title: texas yum-yum cake
directions: Mix the flour, oleo and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: lime delight
directions: Mix crumbs and butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
Whip cold milk until fluffy.
Whip jello until fluffy and fold in sugar, lime and lemon juice.
Then fold jello mixture into whipped milk.
Pour over cookie crumbs.
Sprinkle shaved chocolate over all.
Chill in fridge.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix and beat for 4 minutes. Bake in prepared pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 325°. Cool. Frost with Dream Whip and 1 box pistachio pudding.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix last four ingredients together.
Layer over the browned pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: easy vegetable soup(serves 4)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the tomatoes, carrots, onion, celery, bay leaves and garlic.
Add water and bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add green beans and cook until beans are just tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add zucchini and simmer until tender.
Stir in parsley.
Calorie Count:
100 per serving (2 vegetable exchanges).

title: picante sauce
directions: *Our sauce has 2 dozen in it.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, garlic and green pepper in butter or oleo, cooking until soft over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Peel tomatoes and cut into eighths.
Add tomatoes, salt, bay leaves, pepper and cayenne and continue to cook, uncovered, for about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add shrimp; cover and cook 10 minutes longer. Remove bay leaves and serve at once on hot rice.

title: cream cheese herb spread
directions: With a food processor or electric mixer, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate for an hour or more for flavor to develop and blend.

title: cheese barbecue
directions: Grind cheese, pepper, onion, eggs and olives together.
Add tomato soup and butter.
Mix well and spread on bun or rye bread and broil.
Serves 12.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Trim crusts
and cut bread into cubes.
Melt cheese and margarine in
double
boiler
until
thick and creamy.
Remove from heat and
fold
in
egg whites.
Dip cubes in mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight (may be frozen). Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 30.

title: old fashion sweet dough
directions: Melt Crisco.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix, then add flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Add milk and more flour until hard enough to roll.
Cut into squares and fill with favorite pie filling.
May be used as a pie shell.
Makes great old fashion sweet potato pies.
Makes a lot.

title: jello cake
directions: Make the cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is baking, mix the jello with the boiling water.
When cake is done and has cooled slightly, prick all over with a fork and pour jello over.
Cool and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken salad mold
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in boiling water.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in softened gelatin mixture, salt and pepper.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Add mayonnaise; stir until blended.
Fold in remaining ingredients; pour into a lightly oiled 5 cup mold.
Chill salad until firm. Yields 6 servings.

title: party ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook noodles as directed for 3 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine soup and milk, stirring until smooth.
Add onion, mustard and sour cream, stirring to combine well.
In prepared casserole, layer half the noodles, ham and sauce.
Repeat.
Toss bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over casserole and top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix coca and sugar in 6 quart boiler.
Add milk.
Bring mixture to a boil on stove.
Boil 1 minute at rolling boil.
Take off stove, stir in oleo, vanilla and peanut butter until melted.
Add oats, mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Makes 72 to 80 drop cookies.

title: spoon breads(serve with roast and gravy)
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add shortening and salt.
Stir in meal gradually and cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly. Allow to cool.
Stir in milk, egg yolks and baking powder.
Pour in well-greased shallow baking dish.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 45 minutes.
Cover for first half of cooking time.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in ungreased pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in Bundt pan or 1 hour in loaf pan.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda and salt.
In a bowl, mix the pumpkin and sugar.
Add flour mixture; fold in egg whites and Grape-Nuts.
Mix well.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook beef in enough water to cover same until meat is tender. Peel and cut up potatoes, carrots and onions.
Add vegetables to beef and if needed, add more water.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato juice and bring to a boil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for about 20 minutes to blend tomato juice with other ingredients.
Serves about 6.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Mix gelatin with hot water.
Whip in sour cream.
Add oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, pecans and coconut; mix well.
Pour into a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Chill several hours, or until mixture is set.

title: somemores s'more
directions: Toast marshmallow to golden brown.
Place into sandwich between the chocolate and the two crackers.
Press together and eat.

title: caramel icebox pie
directions: Unwrap and melt caramels in hot water in top of a double boiler.
Add sour cream or softened cream cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: stuffed green peppers(microwave recipe)
directions: Cut a slice from stem end of each pepper.
Remove seeds and membrane.
Combine salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, rice, eggs, 3/4 cup soup, onion and ground beef.
Stir lightly.
Pack each pepper with 1/2 cup of mixture.
Place filled peppers in a round microwave casserole.
(Peppers should fit tightly.)
Pour remaining soup over filled peppers.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave at High 15 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand, covered, for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until light and fluffy. Sift soda, flour, baking powder and salt to mix. Add vanilla and remaining ingredients.
Shape into walnut size balls and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° until brown and done.

title: beans glorioso
directions: Cook on stove for 1 to 2 hours or cook in a crock-pot until they are cooked down.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine first four ingredients and let set 3 or 4 minutes. Then stir until sugar and yeast are dissolved.
Add one beaten egg and Crisco.
Add flour, slowly.
Knead for a few minutes.

title: miracle icing
directions: Mix sugar, egg white and cream of tartar together.
Add boiling water.
Beat on high speed of electric mixer until stiff.
Add vanilla; spread on cake.
This will generously frost and fill an 8 or 9-inch cake.

title: rice dressing
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth until rice is done. Set aside. Cook giblets in 1/2 cup water until tender, then chop. Cook sausage in skillet. Remove from skillet and reserve drippings. Saute garlic, onion, bell pepper and celery about 7 minutes until tender. Add remaining spices. Combine all ingredients in large baking dish. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: creamy microwave round steak
directions: Dredge steak in flour and place in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Top with onion slices.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over steak.
Cover.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) power for 25 minutes. Turn meat over and rearrange pieces.
Baste with the sauce. Re-cover.
Microwave 20 to 30 minutes longer or until meat is fork-tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add milk and corn.
If there is any liquid on corn, drain before adding.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until set.

title: light-as-a-feather gingerbread
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
Add sugar, molasses and beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and beat until smooth. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Good with applesauce.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 medium 8-inch flowerpot, 1 new trowel, 3 large gummy worms and plastic flowers.

title: mountain high cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This makes 3 layers.

title: meatballs and sauerkraut
directions: Cook all sauce ingredients for 15 minutes. Then add meatballs (no need to brown them).
Cook 2 hours on top of stove. Freeze well.
